{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GhWS8AL3THFsgwtxG51ZMq","type":"tool_result","content":"=== processor.rs (TobProcessor + dedup usage) ===\n19:        arbiter::{StalenessFloor, WindowedDedup},\n38:/// Recent trade IDs remembered per (venue, symbol) for cross-publisher trade dedup. Const for now;\n39:/// promote to config alongside the multi-publisher trade test that can size it.\n42:/// The raw top-of-book identity of a quote, used as the per-tick content key for the quote dedup\n44:/// `source_ts` (tracked separately by the floor): two BBOs with the same raw ints but different\n46:/// false-dedup them. Identical content at the same `source_ts` — a republish or the other\n47:/// publisher's copy — is a true duplicate.\n61:/// agree on precision, so a disagreement is a publisher inconsistency worth surfacing rather than\n85:pub struct TobProcessor {\n87:    /// Per-publisher, per-channel frame sequence tracker. Independent publishers mirror this feed\n88:    /// onto one group sharing `channel_id=0`, so a single tracker would mark the slower publisher's\n89:    /// frames stale and drop them before dedup; keying by source IP keeps each publisher's sequence\n92:    /// Log the manifest `Valid=0` publisher workaround once, not on every (~1/s) manifest.\n98:    /// Cross-publisher quote dedup: a per-(venue, symbol) `source_ts` latch-to-leader floor keyed on\n99:    /// raw BBO content and the source IP. Within one `source_ts` tick it emits only the leader (first\n100:    /// publisher to open the tick) and drops other publishers' samples, because arrival order across\n101:    /// delayed publishers can't be trusted (a slower publisher's older sample landing last would read\n103:    /// `(source_ts, content)` repeats. Output `source_ts` is non-decreasing per (venue, symbol).\n104:    quote_dedup: StalenessFloor<(String, String), QuoteContent, IpAddr>,\n105:    /// Cross-publisher trade dedup by venue trade_id per (venue, symbol).\n106:    trade_dedup: WindowedDedup<(String, String), u64>,\n117:            quote_dedup: StalenessFloor::new(),\n118:            trade_dedup: WindowedDedup::new(TRADE_DEDUP_WINDOW),\n123:    /// true if `source_ts` is at or beyond the floor AND (it opens a new tick, or `publisher` is the\n124:    /// tick's latched leader and the `content` is new). Drops strictly-older (stale laggard) BBOs,\n125:    /// non-leader samples within a tick, and the leader's exact `(source_ts, content)` repeats.\n126:    fn admit_quote(\n130:        source_ts: u64,\n131:        content: QuoteContent,\n132:        publisher: IpAddr,\n134:        self.quote_dedup.admit(\n136:            source_ts,\n137:            content,\n138:            publisher,\n143:    fn admit_trade(&mut self, venue: &str, symbol: &str, trade_id: u64) -> bool {\n144:        self.trade_dedup\n145:            .is_new((venue.to_string(), symbol.to_string()), trade_id)\n154:                warn!(role = ?ctx.role, \"decode error: {e}\");\n159:        let handle_refdata = ctx.role.handles_refdata();\n160:        let handle_quotes = ctx.role.handles_mktdata();\n167:        // a `Reset Count` change signals a publisher reset. On the quote feed we drop only the stale\n173:            match self.seq.entry(ctx.publisher).or_default().check(\n180:                        venue = ctx.venue,\n189:                        venue = ctx.venue,\n206:                    // TEMP WORKAROUND: the live DZ Edge HL publisher currently emits\n212:                    // Until the publisher is fixed to emit Valid=1, force valid=true here so\n214:                    // override and pass `m.valid` once the publisher manifest is corrected.\n220:                            \"manifest Valid=0 from publisher; overriding to valid (temporary, logged once)\"\n228:                        venue: ctx.venue.to_string(),\n235:                    upsert_instrument(ctx.instruments, &inst);\n237:                    let _ = ctx.tx.send(FeedMessage::Instrument(inst));\n267:                        if name != ctx.venue && !self.warned_source_mismatch {\n270:                                source_id = q.source_id, registry_venue = name, feed_venue = %ctx.venue,\n280:                        venue: source_name(q.source_id).unwrap_or(ctx.venue).to_string(),\n286:                        source_ts_ns: q.source_ts,\n287:                        recv_ts_ns: ctx.recv_ts_ns,\n288:                        kernel_rx_ts_ns: ctx.kernel_rx_ts_ns,\n291:                    // Cross-publisher dedup on a per-(venue, symbol) source_ts latch-to-leader floor:\n292:                    // within one source_ts tick only the leader (first publisher to open it) is\n293:                    // emitted — a slower publisher's samples at the same tick arrive in a","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e0cfeb0-baf3-4b7d-9735-46f33d7f33c8","uuid":"5f8dc5be-71c9-4a48-b696-3cc62095e0a3","timestamp":"2026-06-18T03:08:32.870Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"=== processor.rs (TobProcessor + dedup usage) ===\n19:        arbiter::{StalenessFloor, WindowedDedup},\n38:/// Recent trade IDs remembered per (venue, symbol) for cross-publisher trade dedup. Const for now;\n39:/// promote to config alongside the multi-publisher trade test that can size it.\n42:/// The raw top-of-book identity of a quote, used as the per-tick content key for the quote dedup\n44:/// `source_ts` (tracked separately by the floor): two BBOs with the same raw ints but different\n46:/// false-dedup them. Identical content at the same `source_ts` — a republish or the other\n47:/// publisher's copy — is a true duplicate.\n61:/// agree on precision, so a disagreement is a publisher inconsistency worth surfacing rather than\n85:pub struct TobProcessor {\n87:    /// Per-publisher, per-channel frame sequence tracker. Independent publishers mirror this feed\n88:    /// onto one group sharing `channel_id=0`, so a single tracker would mark the slower publisher's\n89:    /// frames stale and drop them before dedup; keying by source IP keeps each publisher's sequence\n92:    /// Log the manifest `Valid=0` publisher workaround once, not on every (~1/s) manifest.\n98:    /// Cross-publisher quote dedup: a per-(venue, symbol) `source_ts` latch-to-leader floor keyed on\n99:    /// raw BBO content and the source IP. Within one `source_ts` tick it emits only the leader (first\n100:    /// publisher to open the tick) and drops other publishers' samples, because arrival order across\n101:    /// delayed publishers can't be trusted (a slower publisher's older sample landing last would read\n103:    /// `(source_ts, content)` repeats. Output `source_ts` is non-decreasing per (venue, symbol).\n104:    quote_dedup: StalenessFloor<(String, String), QuoteContent, IpAddr>,\n105:    /// Cross-publisher trade dedup by venue trade_id per (venue, symbol).\n106:    trade_dedup: WindowedDedup<(String, String), u64>,\n117:            quote_dedup: StalenessFloor::new(),\n118:            trade_dedup: WindowedDedup::new(TRADE_DEDUP_WINDOW),\n123:    /// true if `source_ts` is at or beyond the floor AND (it opens a new tick, or `publisher` is the\n124:    /// tick's latched leader and the `content` is new). Drops strictly-older (stale laggard) BBOs,\n125:    /// non-leader samples within a tick, and the leader's exact `(source_ts, content)` repeats.\n126:    fn admit_quote(\n130:        source_ts: u64,\n131:        content: QuoteContent,\n132:        publisher: IpAddr,\n134:        self.quote_dedup.admit(\n136:            source_ts,\n137:            content,\n138:            publisher,\n143:    fn admit_trade(&mut self, venue: &str, symbol: &str, trade_id: u64) -> bool {\n144:        self.trade_dedup\n145:            .is_new((venue.to_string(), symbol.to_string()), trade_id)\n154:                warn!(role = ?ctx.role, \"decode error: {e}\");\n159:        let handle_refdata = ctx.role.handles_refdata();\n160:        let handle_quotes = ctx.role.handles_mktdata();\n167:       