{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AbBEhqjMUaUv3AGh7AsP58","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Work Plan — Issue #8: Phase 3 WebSocket input feeder for public-API arbitrage\n2\t\n3\t> Roadbike planning artifact. Not committed (git-excluded via `.git/info/exclude`)."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e0cfeb0-baf3-4b7d-9735-46f33d7f33c8","uuid":"dbb98a05-4556-4d56-81b0-0cf5b63e4d5d","timestamp":"2026-06-18T03:12:12.946Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/home/claude/workspace/repos/doublezero-edge-connect/docs/work-plan-8.md","content":"# Work Plan — Issue #8: Phase 3 WebSocket input feeder for public-API arbitrage\n\n> Roadbike planning artifact. Not committed (git-excluded via `.git/info/exclude`).","numLines":3,"startLine":1,"totalLines":253}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_014QojJ4pKHUCL94CLVhmKdW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I'll overwrite it."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":328,"cache_read_input_tokens":69069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":328},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e0cfeb0-baf3-4b7d-9735-46f33d7f33c8","uuid":"9437dcfd-3434-4eec-9b44-8b5ef60d7608","request_id":"req_011Cc9zc8XHpxaVQByWajx98"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_014QojJ4pKHUCL94CLVhmKdW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DoP2Vdr6gVtppP8wgQorUJ","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/claude/workspace/repos/doublezero-edge-connect/docs/work-plan-8.md","content":"# Work Plan — Issue #8: Phase 3 WebSocket input feeder for public-API arbitrage\n\n> Roadbike planning artifact. Not committed (git-excluded via `.git/info/exclude`).\n> **Revision 2** — rewritten against the **updated base PR #29** (head `de61ad5`), which replaced the\n> strict watermark with a **latch-to-leader floor** (`StalenessFloor<K, V, P>`) keyed on a publisher\n> `P`. Operator steer: the public HL feed becomes **just another publisher racing for each slot** in\n> that existing floor — no new dedup primitive, and the content-identity question is now moot (see\n> \"The content-identity question, resolved\").\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd the Hyperliquid **public** BBO/trades feed (`wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws`) as a second ingest\nsource that emits the same `FeedMessage`s into the same broadcast channel as the DZ Edge multicast\npipeline. PR #29 already turned the quote path into a **per-`(venue, symbol)` latch-to-leader floor**:\nwithin one `source_ts` tick, only the *leader* publisher (the first to open that tick) is emitted and\nevery other publisher's sample at that tick is dropped; the leader is re-selected each new tick. The\nedge multicast publishers already race through this floor by source IP.\n\nThe whole of this issue is therefore: **make the public WS feed one more publisher in that same\nfloor.** Because the edge publishers deliver each `source_ts` tick with sub-millisecond delay and the\npublic feed arrives tens of milliseconds later over the internet, an edge publisher essentially always\nopens (leads) each tick, so the public copy at that tick is dropped as a non-leader. When the edge\nfeed gaps or stalls, no edge publisher opens the next tick, so the public feed's sample is the first to\ncross the floor (`source_ts > high_water`) — it leads and fills in. That is the backstop, and it falls\nout of the existing floor with **no health check and no content matching**. The WebSocket **output**\ncontract (PROTOCOL.md) is unchanged.\n\nThe one structural change: PR #29's floor lives **inside `TobProcessor`**, and there is one processor\nper multicast feed. For the public feed to race in the *same* floor as the edge HL feed (so their\ncopies collapse instead of both reaching the WS as duplicates), the floor — and the trade\n`WindowedDedup` — must be **lifted into a process-wide shared arbiter** that both the multicast\nprocessors and the WS feeder funnel through. That refactor is Stage A.\n\n## Base-PR status / rebase note\n\nMy branch (`bdz/doublezero-edge-connect-8`) is currently tipped at the **old** PR #29 design\n(`6fc5463`, \"freshest-wins source_ts watermark\"). PR #29 has since been force-updated to the\n**latch-to-leader** design (`de61ad5`). **This work rebases onto the new PR #29 head**; the strict\n`Watermark` no longer exists in the tree and there is nothing to remove — the floor already ships.\nThe arbiter primitives (`StalenessFloor`, `WindowedDedup`) live in `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` today as\nplain primitives owned by `TobProcessor`; Stage A promotes them to a shared emit stage. #8 closes with\nthis single PR.\n\n## What changed since revision 1\n\nRevision 1 was written against the *watermark* PR #29 and invented a \"staleness floor + content\nidentity\" primitive plus an elaborate \"rescale public px/sz to the edge's canonical exponents so the\ntwo BBO tuples are bit-equal\" requirement, because under a content-keyed merge the public and edge\ncopies had to hash identically to collapse. **All of that is now deleted.** Under latch-to-leader:\n\n- The floor **already exists** (`StalenessFloor`) — I reuse it, I do not write a new primitive.\n- Cross-source dedup is decided by **publisher leadership per tick**, never by content. So the public\n  feed's px/sz do **not** need to match the edge's bit-for-bit, the canonical-exponent rescale is\n  gone, and the FNV/`StableBBOHash` bit-compat discussion is irrelevant (not deferred — moot).\n- The public feeder shrinks accordingly: it parses HL decimal strings straight to real-unit `f64`s\n  (the same units `apply_exponent` produces on the edge side) and emits.\n\n## The content-identity question, resolved\n\nThe operator asked for a clearer explanation or a good default on content identity. Here it is, then\nthe choice:\n\nTrace `StalenessFloor::admit(key, source_ts, content, publisher)` for a tick that is already open\n(`source_ts == high_water`):\n\n- if `publisher != leader` → **dropped immediately; `content` is never looked at.**\n- if `publisher == leader` → admit iff `content` is new **in the leader's own set** (drops that one\n  publisher's exact repeats).\n\nSo `content` is only ever compared **within a single publisher's own stream**. Two different\npublishers' contents are *never* compared to each other — the non-leader loses on identity before\ncontent is consulted. Therefore the public feed's content does **not** need to equal the edge feed's\ncontent for the same update; there is nothing to make bit-compatible.\n\n**Choice (default, operator can override):** drop the cross-source content-matching requirement and\nthe canonical-exponent rescale entirely. The public feeder computes content the same uniform way every\nquote does (over the normalized BBO `f64`s), purely so the floor can drop the public feed's *own*\nexact repeats when the public feed happens to be the leader (during an edge gap). px/sz are parsed to\nreal-unit `f64`s directly. *If* a future requirement needs the live bridge and the offline\n`hl-bbo-feed-race` board to dedup on a byte-identical key, that is a separate follow-up; it is not\nneeded for this issue's correctness or acceptance criteria.\n\n## Key context discovered during planning (against `de61ad5`)\n\n- **Floor + send live in `TobProcessor`.** `src/ingest/processor.rs`:\n  `quote_dedup: StalenessFloor<(String, String), QuoteContent, IpAddr>` and\n  `trade_dedup: WindowedDedup<(String, String), u64>`. Emission is\n  `if self.admit_quote(...) { ctx.tx.send(FeedMessage::Quote(quote)) }` (and the trade analog). There\n  is **one processor per feed**, so today each feed has its own private floor — fine for the edge's\n  two source-IP publishers (same processor, same group), but the public WS feed is a *separate task*\n  and would have a *separate* floor unless we share it.\n- **`FrameCtx`** (`src/ingest/receiver.rs:81`) carries `tx: &broadcast::Sender<FeedMessage>`,\n  `instruments: &InstrumentSnapshot`, and `publisher: IpAddr` (the datagram source IP — the existing\n  per-publisher demux key). `drive()`/`run_feed()` thread these in; `emit_status` sends straight on\n  `tx`.\n- **`publisher: P` is the floor's leader identity.** Today `P = IpAddr`. The public feed has no\n  multicast source IP, so the shared floor's `P` becomes a small `Publisher` enum\n  (`Edge(IpAddr)` | `PublicWs`) — the edge path wraps `ctx.publisher`, the feeder uses `PublicWs`.\n- **Units already line up.** Edge quotes are real-unit `f64`s via `apply_exponent(raw, exponent)`;\n  HL public px/sz are decimal strings in real units. `\"104783.0\".parse::<f64>()` lands in the same\n  unit space, so when the public feed leads during a gap, consumers see consistent magnitudes — no\n  rescale needed.\n- **Precision-before-price for the public feed** comes from the shared `InstrumentSnapshot`\n  (`Mutex<HashMap>` keyed `(venue, symbol)`), which the edge refdata populates. The feeder gates each\n  public quote on the `(venue, symbol)` instrument being present in that snapshot — the realistic\n  backstop scenario is edge **refdata healthy while mktdata stalls**. Standalone-public (no edge\n  refdata ever) is a documented limitation, deferred.\n- **TLS for the outbound client.** `tokio-tungstenite = \"0.29\"` is present (used as a WS *server* by\n  the sink, no TLS feature). The `wss://` *client* needs a `rustls`-based feature enabled in\n  `Cargo.toml` (confirm the exact 0.29 feature name during implementation; pick the webpki-roots\n  variant for a portable container with no system OpenSSL).\n\n## Approach (single PR, three internal commits A → B → C)\n\n**A. Lift the floor + trade dedup into a shared pre-broadcast arbiter (the core refactor).**\nPromote `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` from \"primitives owned by the processor\" to a shared emit stage. Add\nan `Arbiter` that owns the `broadcast::Sender<FeedMessage>` **plus** the dedup state — the existing\n`StalenessFloor` for quotes (keyed `(venue, symbol)`, `P = Publisher`) and the existing `WindowedDedup`\nfor trades — and exposes one entry point `emit(msg, publisher)`: it applies the floor to `Quote`\n(computing the content identity over the normalized BBO `f64`s), the windowed dedup to `Trade` (on\n`trade_id`), and passes `Instrument`/`Depth`/`Midpoint`/`Status` straight through. Wrap it\n`Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>` (`SharedArbiter`) so every multicast receiver task **and** the new WS feeder\nfunnel through one instance per process — one floor per `(venue, symbol)`, so the edge HL processor and\nthe public feeder converge on the *same* floor and race. Introduce the `Publisher` enum. `FrameCtx`\nswaps its raw `tx` for the arbiter handle (or an `emit` path); `TobProcessor` loses\n`quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup`/`admit_quote`/`admit_trade`/`QuoteContent` and calls `ctx.emit(...)`,\nwrapping `ctx.publisher` as `Publisher::Edge(ip)`. `emit_status` routes through the arbiter\npassthrough. The WS sink keeps `tx.subscribe()` unchanged (the arbiter exposes the `Sender`). The\n`StalenessFloor`/`WindowedDedup` unit tests move with the primitives; the content-identity unit (raw\n`QuoteContent`) becomes a content-over-normalized-`f64`s unit. **No behavior change to the edge path**\n— this is a relocation; the latch-to-leader semantics are identical.\n\n**B. WS-client feeder task (the new ingest source).**\nNew module `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` connects to `wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws` over TLS, sends one\n`{\"method\":\"subscribe\",\"subscription\":{\"type\":\"bbo\",\"coin\":\"<C>\"}}` and one `trades` subscription per\ncarried coin over a **single shared connection** (HL has no wildcard; check the documented\nper-connection subscription cap and log if the configured coin set would exceed it), decodes HL\n`bbo`/`trades` JSON into `FeedMessage::Quote`/`Trade` (venue `\"Hyperliquid\"`, public block `time` ms →\n`source_ts_ns = time * 1_000_000` so it shares the **same canonical `source_ts`** as the edge copy —\nthis is what puts both copies in the *same* floor tick; `tid` → `trade_id`), parses px/sz decimal\nstrings to real-unit `f64`s, **gates on the `(venue, symbol)` instrument being present in the shared\n`InstrumentSnapshot`** (precision before price), and calls `arbiter.emit(msg, Publisher::PublicWs)`.\nIt runs as its own `tokio::spawn`ed task with **reconnect + exponential backoff**; all decode/socket\nerrors are swallowed (logged) so the multicast hot path is never touched. **Off by default**, gated on\na non-empty config value per the repo's source/sink activation convention. A `--ws-input-url` override\npoints the feeder at a local mock for the E2E.\n\n**C. Mock-WS input harness + backstop E2E (mostly tests).**\nA tiny in-test HL WS server / scripted driver (`tests/common/ws_input.rs`) that plays scripted\n`bbo`/`trades` JSON; reuse `ws_client` + `assertions` unchanged on the output side. Two E2E cases:\n**edge-leads-in-steady-state** (edge + public both fed the same `source_ts` ticks; public dropped as a\nnon-leader; `no_business_duplicates` green, `source_ts` non-decreasing) and **edge-gap → public leads**\n(edge mktdata withheld; public opens the new ticks and is emitted).\n\n## Files to change / create\n\n### Stage A — shared arbiter (refactor; **behavior-preserving** for the edge path)\n- `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` — add `pub enum Publisher { Edge(IpAddr), PublicWs }`; switch the\n  `StalenessFloor`'s `P` at the call sites to `Publisher` (the primitive is already generic over\n  `P: Eq`). Add `struct Arbiter { tx, quotes: StalenessFloor<(String,String), QuoteId, Publisher>,\n  trades: WindowedDedup<(String,String), u64> }` with `emit(&mut self, msg, publisher)` and a\n  `sender()` accessor; `type SharedArbiter = Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>`. Define `QuoteId` as a stable hash /\n  bit-tuple over the normalized BBO `f64`s. Keep all existing floor/windowed unit tests; migrate the\n  content unit to `QuoteId`. *(~90–120 lines net.)*\n- `src/ingest/receiver.rs` — `FrameCtx` carries the arbiter handle (or an `emit` path) instead of a\n  raw `tx`; `drive()`/`run_feed()` thread `SharedArbiter` through; `emit_status` routes through the\n  arbiter passthrough. *(~30 lines.)*\n- `src/ingest/processor.rs` — drop `quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup`/`admit_quote`/`admit_trade` and the raw\n  `QuoteContent` from `TobProcessor`; replace `if self.admit_quote(...) { ctx.tx.send(...) }` with\n  `ctx.emit(FeedMessage::Quote(quote), Publisher::Edge(ctx.publisher))` (trade analog).\n  `MidpointProcessor`/`MboProcessor` emit through `ctx` too (passthrough). Move the in-processor dedup\n  unit tests to the arbiter. *(~40 lines changed, net reduction.)*\n- `src/main.rs` — build `SharedArbiter` around the broadcast `Sender`; pass it to each receiver; the\n  WS sink still gets `tx.subscribe()` via `arbiter.sender()`. *(~10 lines.)*\n- `tests/dedup.rs` — re-target the existing two-publisher latch-to-leader assertions to the shared\n  arbiter (semantics unchanged; only the owner moved). *(tests, excluded from count.)*\n\n### Stage B — WS feeder + TLS + wiring (the new ingest source)\n- `Cargo.toml` — enable a `rustls`-based `tokio-tungstenite` TLS feature (webpki-roots; no system\n  OpenSSL); confirm the exact 0.29 feature name during implementation. *(deps.)*\n- `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` (new) — HL JSON structs (`bbo`, `trades`), single-connection connect +\n  per-coin subscribe fan-out (log if the coin set exceeds HL's documented subscription cap), decode →\n  `FeedMessage`, public `time` ms → `source_ts_ns`, decimal-string px/sz → real-unit `f64`,\n  `(venue, symbol)` instrument-presence gate against the shared `InstrumentSnapshot`,\n  reconnect/backoff, error isolation, `emit(msg, Publisher::PublicWs)`, `--ws-input-url` override.\n  *(~150–180 lines — smaller than rev. 1, no rescale machinery.)*\n- `src/ingest/mod.rs` — `pub mod ws_feeder;`. *(1 line.)*\n- `src/main.rs` — `--ws-input-coins` / `--ws-input-url` flags (+ env `WS_INPUT_COINS`/`WS_INPUT_URL`),\n  spawn the feeder when the coin list is non-empty, include it in the `select!`/`JoinSet` lifecycle.\n  *(~30 lines.)*\n\n### Stage C — mock-WS input harness + backstop E2E (mostly tests)\n- `tests/common/ws_input.rs` (new) + `tests/common/mod.rs` — mock HL WS server / scripted driver.\n  *(tests, excluded.)*\n- `tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs` (new) — edge-leads-in-steady-state + edge-gap→public-leads.\n  *(tests, excluded.)*\n\n### Docs (excluded from line count)\n- `README.md` — new **input source** subsection + flag/env row for the WS feeder (distinct from the\n  output-sink table); off by default, backstop-by-racing semantics.\n- `CHANGELOG.md` — `[Unreleased] / Added` (public WS input feeder; shared arbiter emit stage).\n- `CLAUDE.md` — document the shared arbiter stage (floor + trade dedup lifted out of `TobProcessor`),\n  the `Publisher` enum, the `ws_feeder` module, and that ingest now has two source transports\n  (multicast + WS feeder) converging on one floor that races them per `(venue, symbol)` tick; note\n  PROTOCOL.md is unchanged.\n- `PROTOCOL.md` — **no change** (output contract unchanged); state this explicitly in the PR.\n\n## Risks & considerations\n\n- **Refactor is behavior-preserving for the edge path** (unlike rev. 1, which changed dedup\n  semantics). Stage A only relocates the existing latch-to-leader floor and trade dedup into a shared\n  owner. The two-publisher `tests/dedup.rs` assertions and the floor unit tests must stay green\n  byte-for-byte in semantics after the move — that is the guardrail.\n- **The public feed leads only on a genuine gap.** Correctness of the backstop rests on the edge\n  publishers reliably opening each `source_ts` tick first (sub-ms vs. tens of ms). If public ever\n  beats the edge for a tick (e.g. a brief edge hiccup), public leads that one tick and edge's later\n  same-`source_ts` samples are dropped as non-leader — acceptable (still fresh, single-source-coherent\n  within the tick), and self-corrects at the next tick. Worth a sentence in the PR.\n- **Recovery after a gap.** During a gap the public feed advances `high_water` to `T_public`. When the\n  edge resumes, its frames with `source_ts < T_public` are dropped as stale until edge catches past\n  `T_public`. Because `source_ts` is the shared venue block time, edge catches up within a tick or two\n  — correct (never regress to older edge data). Note it; do not special-case it.\n- **Shared mutable state across tasks.** The arbiter is on the emit path of every receiver and the\n  feeder; tasks now contend on one `Mutex` instead of each owning private state. Keep the critical\n  section tiny (the admit decision + send) and `emit` panic-free (no `unwrap` on feed data) so a panic\n  can't poison the lock. The single-receiver common path stays uncontended.\n- **Public-feed failure isolation.** Reconnect storms / decode errors must never block multicast. The\n  feeder is a separate task; failures back off and retry, never propagate.\n- **Instrument-definition availability.** A public quote needs its `(venue, symbol)` instrument in the\n  snapshot to satisfy precision-before-price. We rely on edge refdata being healthy while mktdata\n  stalls (the realistic backstop). Document the assumption + the standalone-public limitation.\n- **Unbounded public lag.** A long public reconnect can deliver very stale `source_ts`, which the floor\n  rejects (`< high_water`) — correct in steady state, but a public copy that is *both* stale and\n  arrives during an edge gap could be dropped. This is the window/lag failure mode the issue defers to\n  **#30** (window sizing); call it out, do not solve it here.\n- **TLS dependency surface.** Pick the `rustls`/webpki-roots feature (no system OpenSSL) for portable\n  container builds.\n- **HL subscription/connection limits.** Verify the documented per-connection subscription cap and\n  fan-out within one connection; log if the configured coin set would exceed it.\n\n## Testing strategy\n\n- `cargo test` — existing codec round-trips, refdata state machine, and the two-publisher\n  latch-to-leader tests (`tests/dedup.rs`) stay green after the floor/trade-dedup move to the arbiter.\n- Arbiter unit tests (migrated from the processor + primitives): leader latch within a tick, non-leader\n  drop, stale-tick drop for any publisher, new-tick re-latch, per-`(venue, symbol)` independence, and a\n  **`Publisher::PublicWs` loses to `Publisher::Edge` at the same tick** case (the steady-state backstop\n  in miniature); trade `trade_id` windowed dedup unchanged.\n- New E2E (`tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs`): drive the release binary with both the multicast replayer\n  and the mock WS input driver; assert `no_business_duplicates` + `source_ts` non-decreasing for the\n  steady-state case, and public emission for the edge-gap case.\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets` and `cargo fmt` clean.\n\n## Estimated scope (single PR)\n\n| Stage | Area | Est. lines added (code, non-test/doc) |\n|------|------|------------------------|\n| A | lift floor + trade dedup into shared arbiter + `Publisher` enum | ~120–150 |\n| B | WS feeder (parse-to-`f64`, no rescale) + TLS + wiring | ~180–210 |\n| C | harness + E2E | ~0–20 code (mostly tests) |\n| **Total** | | **~300–380** |\n\nComfortably under the 500-line threshold — ships as **one PR** with three internal commits (A → B → C)\nfor review legibility, per work-fast mode. #8 closes with it. (Lower than rev. 1: the floor already\nexists and the canonical-exponent rescale is gone.)\n\n## Open questions (defaults assumed; operator can override at re-review)\n\n1. **Content identity** — resolved to a default: under latch-to-leader, content is only ever compared\n   within one publisher's own stream, so the public feed needs **no** bit-compatible content and **no**\n   canonical-exponent rescale. The feeder parses px/sz to real-unit `f64`s and lets the floor's\n   publisher-leadership decide every cross-source race. Override only if you need the live bridge and\n   the offline `hl-bbo-feed-race` board to dedup on a byte-identical key now (separate follow-up).\n2. **Publisher identity type** — assumed a small `enum Publisher { Edge(IpAddr), PublicWs }` for the\n   floor's `P`, leaving the multicast `SeqTracker` keyed on `IpAddr` as today. Override if you'd rather\n   give the public feed a sentinel `IpAddr` and keep `P = IpAddr` (smaller diff, less self-documenting).\n3. **Shared arbiter vs. share-only-the-floor** — assumed the clean shared `Arbiter` emit stage (admit +\n   send in one place). The lighter alternative is to inject just the `Arc<Mutex<StalenessFloor>>` +\n   `Arc<Mutex<WindowedDedup>>` into both `TobProcessor` and the feeder and keep the `ctx.tx.send` call\n   sites. The arbiter is cleaner and centralizes the emit decision; flag if you prefer the minimal\n   injection.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":328,"cache_read_input_tokens":69069,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":328},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e0cfeb0-baf3-4b7d-9735-46f33d7f33c8","uuid":"04ccda3e-2a1e-462f-aaf3-1f2723abb080","request_id":"req_011Cc9zc8XHpxaVQByWajx98"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DoP2Vdr6gVtppP8wgQorUJ","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /home/claude/workspace/repos/doublezero-edge-connect/docs/work-plan-8.md has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e0cfeb0-baf3-4b7d-9735-46f33d7f33c8","uuid":"389c1e50-3e32-4b8f-968d-e34950014557","timestamp":"2026-06-18T03:13:37.710Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"update","filePath":"/home/claude/workspace/repos/doublezero-edge-connect/docs/work-plan-8.md","content":"# Work Plan — Issue #8: Phase 3 WebSocket input feeder for public-API arbitrage\n\n> Roadbike planning artifact. Not committed (git-excluded via `.git/info/exclude`).\n> **Revision 2** — rewritten against the **updated base PR #29** (head `de61ad5`), which replaced the\n> strict watermark with a **latch-to-leader floor** (`StalenessFloor<K, V, P>`) keyed on a publisher\n> `P`. Operator steer: the public HL feed becomes **just another publisher racing for each slot** in\n> that existing floor — no new dedup primitive, and the content-identity question is now moot (see\n> \"The content-identity question, resolved\").\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd the Hyperliquid **public** BBO/trades feed (`wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws`) as a second ingest\nsource that emits the same `FeedMessage`s into the same broadcast channel as the DZ Edge multicast\npipeline. PR #29 already turned the quote path into a **per-`(venue, symbol)` latch-to-leader floor**:\nwithin one `source_ts` tick, only the *leader* publisher (the first to open that tick) is emitted and\nevery other publisher's sample at that tick is dropped; the leader is re-selected each new tick. The\nedge multicast publishers already race through this floor by source IP.\n\nThe whole of this issue is therefore: **make the public WS feed one more publisher in that same\nfloor.** Because the edge publishers deliver each `source_ts` tick with sub-millisecond delay and the\npublic feed arrives tens of milliseconds later over the internet, an edge publisher essentially always\nopens (leads) each tick, so the public copy at that tick is dropped as a non-leader. When the edge\nfeed gaps or stalls, no edge publisher opens the next tick, so the public feed's sample is the first to\ncross the floor (`source_ts > high_water`) — it leads and fills in. That is the backstop, and it falls\nout of the existing floor with **no health check and no content matching**. The WebSocket **output**\ncontract (PROTOCOL.md) is unchanged.\n\nThe one structural change: PR #29's floor lives **inside `TobProcessor`**, and there is one processor\nper multicast feed. For the public feed to race in the *same* floor as the edge HL feed (so their\ncopies collapse instead of both reaching the WS as duplicates), the floor — and the trade\n`WindowedDedup` — must be **lifted into a process-wide shared arbiter** that both the multicast\nprocessors and the WS feeder funnel through. That refactor is Stage A.\n\n## Base-PR status / rebase note\n\nMy branch (`bdz/doublezero-edge-connect-8`) is currently tipped at the **old** PR #29 design\n(`6fc5463`, \"freshest-wins source_ts watermark\"). PR #29 has since been force-updated to the\n**latch-to-leader** design (`de61ad5`). **This work rebases onto the new PR #29 head**; the strict\n`Watermark` no longer exists in the tree and there is nothing to remove — the floor already ships.\nThe arbiter primitives (`StalenessFloor`, `WindowedDedup`) live in `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` today as\nplain primitives owned by `TobProcessor`; Stage A promotes them to a shared emit stage. #8 closes with\nthis single PR.\n\n## What changed since revision 1\n\nRevision 1 was written against the *watermark* PR #29 and invented a \"staleness floor + content\nidentity\" primitive plus an elaborate \"rescale public px/sz to the edge's canonical exponents so the\ntwo BBO tuples are bit-equal\" requirement, because under a content-keyed merge the public and edge\ncopies had to hash identically to collapse. **All of that is now deleted.** Under latch-to-leader:\n\n- The floor **already exists** (`StalenessFloor`) — I reuse it, I do not write a new primitive.\n- Cross-source dedup is decided by **publisher leadership per tick**, never by content. So the public\n  feed's px/sz do **not** need to match the edge's bit-for-bit, the canonical-exponent rescale is\n  gone, and the FNV/`StableBBOHash` bit-compat discussion is irrelevant (not deferred — moot).\n- The public feeder shrinks accordingly: it parses HL decimal strings straight to real-unit `f64`s\n  (the same units `apply_exponent` produces on the edge side) and emits.\n\n## The content-identity question, resolved\n\nThe operator asked for a clearer explanation or a good default on content identity. Here it is, then\nthe choice:\n\nTrace `StalenessFloor::admit(key, source_ts, content, publisher)` for a tick that is already open\n(`source_ts == high_water`):\n\n- if `publisher != leader` → **dropped immediately; `content` is never looked at.**\n- if `publisher == leader` → admit iff `content` is new **in the leader's own set** (drops that one\n  publisher's exact repeats).\n\nSo `content` is only ever compared **within a single publisher's own stream**. Two different\npublishers' contents are *never* compared to each other — the non-leader loses on identity before\ncontent is consulted. Therefore the public feed's content does **not** need to equal the edge feed's\ncontent for the same update; there is nothing to make bit-compatible.\n\n**Choice (default, operator can override):** drop the cross-source content-matching requirement and\nthe canonical-exponent rescale entirely. The public feeder computes content the same uniform way every\nquote does (over the normalized BBO `f64`s), purely so the floor can drop the public feed's *own*\nexact repeats when the public feed happens to be the leader (during an edge gap). px/sz are parsed to\nreal-unit `f64`s directly. *If* a future requirement needs the live bridge and the offline\n`hl-bbo-feed-race` board to dedup on a byte-identical key, that is a separate follow-up; it is not\nneeded for this issue's correctness or acceptance criteria.\n\n## Key context discovered during planning (against `de61ad5`)\n\n- **Floor + send live in `TobProcessor`.** `src/ingest/processor.rs`:\n  `quote_dedup: StalenessFloor<(String, String), QuoteContent, IpAddr>` and\n  `trade_dedup: WindowedDedup<(String, String), u64>`. Emission is\n  `if self.admit_quote(...) { ctx.tx.send(FeedMessage::Quote(quote)) }` (and the trade analog). There\n  is **one processor per feed**, so today each feed has its own private floor — fine for the edge's\n  two source-IP publishers (same processor, same group), but the public WS feed is a *separate task*\n  and would have a *separate* floor unless we share it.\n- **`FrameCtx`** (`src/ingest/receiver.rs:81`) carries `tx: &broadcast::Sender<FeedMessage>`,\n  `instruments: &InstrumentSnapshot`, and `publisher: IpAddr` (the datagram source IP — the existing\n  per-publisher demux key). `drive()`/`run_feed()` thread these in; `emit_status` sends straight on\n  `tx`.\n- **`publisher: P` is the floor's leader identity.** Today `P = IpAddr`. The public feed has no\n  multicast source IP, so the shared floor's `P` becomes a small `Publisher` enum\n  (`Edge(IpAddr)` | `PublicWs`) — the edge path wraps `ctx.publisher`, the feeder uses `PublicWs`.\n- **Units already line up.** Edge quotes are real-unit `f64`s via `apply_exponent(raw, exponent)`;\n  HL public px/sz are decimal strings in real units. `\"104783.0\".parse::<f64>()` lands in the same\n  unit space, so when the public feed leads during a gap, consumers see consistent magnitudes — no\n  rescale needed.\n- **Precision-before-price for the public feed** comes from the shared `InstrumentSnapshot`\n  (`Mutex<HashMap>` keyed `(venue, symbol)`), which the edge refdata populates. The feeder gates each\n  public quote on the `(venue, symbol)` instrument being present in that snapshot — the realistic\n  backstop scenario is edge **refdata healthy while mktdata stalls**. Standalone-public (no edge\n  refdata ever) is a documented limitation, deferred.\n- **TLS for the outbound client.** `tokio-tungstenite = \"0.29\"` is present (used as a WS *server* by\n  the sink, no TLS feature). The `wss://` *client* needs a `rustls`-based feature enabled in\n  `Cargo.toml` (confirm the exact 0.29 feature name during implementation; pick the webpki-roots\n  variant for a portable container with no system OpenSSL).\n\n## Approach (single PR, three internal commits A → B → C)\n\n**A. Lift the floor + trade dedup into a shared pre-broadcast arbiter (the core refactor).**\nPromote `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` from \"primitives owned by the processor\" to a shared emit stage. Add\nan `Arbiter` that owns the `broadcast::Sender<FeedMessage>` **plus** the dedup state — the existing\n`StalenessFloor` for quotes (keyed `(venue, symbol)`, `P = Publisher`) and the existing `WindowedDedup`\nfor trades — and exposes one entry point `emit(msg, publisher)`: it applies the floor to `Quote`\n(computing the content identity over the normalized BBO `f64`s), the windowed dedup to `Trade` (on\n`trade_id`), and passes `Instrument`/`Depth`/`Midpoint`/`Status` straight through. Wrap it\n`Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>` (`SharedArbiter`) so every multicast receiver task **and** the new WS feeder\nfunnel through one instance per process — one floor per `(venue, symbol)`, so the edge HL processor and\nthe public feeder converge on the *same* floor and race. Introduce the `Publisher` enum. `FrameCtx`\nswaps its raw `tx` for the arbiter handle (or an `emit` path); `TobProcessor` loses\n`quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup`/`admit_quote`/`admit_trade`/`QuoteContent` and calls `ctx.emit(...)`,\nwrapping `ctx.publisher` as `Publisher::Edge(ip)`. `emit_status` routes through the arbiter\npassthrough. The WS sink keeps `tx.subscribe()` unchanged (the arbiter exposes the `Sender`). The\n`StalenessFloor`/`WindowedDedup` unit tests move with the primitives; the content-identity unit (raw\n`QuoteContent`) becomes a content-over-normalized-`f64`s unit. **No behavior change to the edge path**\n— this is a relocation; the latch-to-leader semantics are identical.\n\n**B. WS-client feeder task (the new ingest source).**\nNew module `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` connects to `wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws` over TLS, sends one\n`{\"method\":\"subscribe\",\"subscription\":{\"type\":\"bbo\",\"coin\":\"<C>\"}}` and one `trades` subscription per\ncarried coin over a **single shared connection** (HL has no wildcard; check the documented\nper-connection subscription cap and log if the configured coin set would exceed it), decodes HL\n`bbo`/`trades` JSON into `FeedMessage::Quote`/`Trade` (venue `\"Hyperliquid\"`, public block `time` ms →\n`source_ts_ns = time * 1_000_000` so it shares the **same canonical `source_ts`** as the edge copy —\nthis is what puts both copies in the *same* floor tick; `tid` → `trade_id`), parses px/sz decimal\nstrings to real-unit `f64`s, **gates on the `(venue, symbol)` instrument being present in the shared\n`InstrumentSnapshot`** (precision before price), and calls `arbiter.emit(msg, Publisher::PublicWs)`.\nIt runs as its own `tokio::spawn`ed task with **reconnect + exponential backoff**; all decode/socket\nerrors are swallowed (logged) so the multicast hot path is never touched. **Off by default**, gated on\na non-empty config value per the repo's source/sink activation convention. A `--ws-input-url` override\npoints the feeder at a local mock for the E2E.\n\n**C. Mock-WS input harness + backstop E2E (mostly tests).**\nA tiny in-test HL WS server / scripted driver (`tests/common/ws_input.rs`) that plays scripted\n`bbo`/`trades` JSON; reuse `ws_client` + `assertions` unchanged on the output side. Two E2E cases:\n**edge-leads-in-steady-state** (edge + public both fed the same `source_ts` ticks; public dropped as a\nnon-leader; `no_business_duplicates` green, `source_ts` non-decreasing) and **edge-gap → public leads**\n(edge mktdata withheld; public opens the new ticks and is emitted).\n\n## Files to change / create\n\n### Stage A — shared arbiter (refactor; **behavior-preserving** for the edge path)\n- `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` — add `pub enum Publisher { Edge(IpAddr), PublicWs }`; switch the\n  `StalenessFloor`'s `P` at the call sites to `Publisher` (the primitive is already generic over\n  `P: Eq`). Add `struct Arbiter { tx, quotes: StalenessFloor<(String,String), QuoteId, Publisher>,\n  trades: WindowedDedup<(String,String), u64> }` with `emit(&mut self, msg, publisher)` and a\n  `sender()` accessor; `type SharedArbiter = Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>`. Define `QuoteId` as a stable hash /\n  bit-tuple over the normalized BBO `f64`s. Keep all existing floor/windowed unit tests; migrate the\n  content unit to `QuoteId`. *(~90–120 lines net.)*\n- `src/ingest/receiver.rs` — `FrameCtx` carries the arbiter handle (or an `emit` path) instead of a\n  raw `tx`; `drive()`/`run_feed()` thread `SharedArbiter` through; `emit_status` routes through the\n  arbiter passthrough. *(~30 lines.)*\n- `src/ingest/processor.rs` — drop `quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup`/`admit_quote`/`admit_trade` and the raw\n  `QuoteContent` from `TobProcessor`; replace `if self.admit_quote(...) { ctx.tx.send(...) }` with\n  `ctx.emit(FeedMessage::Quote(quote), Publisher::Edge(ctx.publisher))` (trade analog).\n  `MidpointProcessor`/`MboProcessor` emit through `ctx` too (passthrough). Move the in-processor dedup\n  unit tests to the arbiter. *(~40 lines changed, net reduction.)*\n- `src/main.rs` — build `SharedArbiter` around the broadcast `Sender`; pass it to each receiver; the\n  WS sink still gets `tx.subscribe()` via `arbiter.sender()`. *(~10 lines.)*\n- `tests/dedup.rs` — re-target the existing two-publisher latch-to-leader assertions to the shared\n  arbiter (semantics unchanged; only the owner moved). *(tests, excluded from count.)*\n\n### Stage B — WS feeder + TLS + wiring (the new ingest source)\n- `Cargo.toml` — enable a `rustls`-based `tokio-tungstenite` TLS feature (webpki-roots; no system\n  OpenSSL); confirm the exact 0.29 feature name during implementation. *(deps.)*\n- `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` (new) — HL JSON structs (`bbo`, `trades`), single-connection connect +\n  per-coin subscribe fan-out (log if the coin set exceeds HL's documented subscription cap), decode →\n  `FeedMessage`, public `time` ms → `source_ts_ns`, decimal-string px/sz → real-unit `f64`,\n  `(venue, symbol)` instrument-presence gate against the shared `InstrumentSnapshot`,\n  reconnect/backoff, error isolation, `emit(msg, Publisher::PublicWs)`, `--ws-input-url` override.\n  *(~150–180 lines — smaller than rev. 1, no rescale machinery.)*\n- `src/ingest/mod.rs` — `pub mod ws_feeder;`. *(1 line.)*\n- `src/main.rs` — `--ws-input-coins` / `--ws-input-url` flags (+ env `WS_INPUT_COINS`/`WS_INPUT_URL`),\n  spawn the feeder when the coin list is non-empty, include it in the `select!`/`JoinSet` lifecycle.\n  *(~30 lines.)*\n\n### Stage C — mock-WS input harness + backstop E2E (mostly tests)\n- `tests/common/ws_input.rs` (new) + `tests/common/mod.rs` — mock HL WS server / scripted driver.\n  *(tests, excluded.)*\n- `tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs` (new) — edge-leads-in-steady-state + edge-gap→public-leads.\n  *(tests, excluded.)*\n\n### Docs (excluded from line count)\n- `README.md` — new **input source** subsection + flag/env row for the WS feeder (distinct from the\n  output-sink table); off by default, backstop-by-racing semantics.\n- `CHANGELOG.md` — `[Unreleased] / Added` (public WS input feeder; shared arbiter emit stage).\n- `CLAUDE.md` — document the shared arbiter stage (floor + trade dedup lifted out of `TobProcessor`),\n  the `Publisher` enum, the `ws_feeder` module, and that ingest now has two source transports\n  (multicast + WS feeder) converging on one floor that races them per `(venue, symbol)` tick; note\n  PROTOCOL.md is unchanged.\n- `PROTOCOL.md` — **no change** (output contract unchanged); state this explicitly in the PR.\n\n## Risks & considerations\n\n- **Refactor is behavior-preserving for the edge path** (unlike rev. 1, which changed dedup\n  semantics). Stage A only relocates the existing latch-to-leader floor and trade dedup into a shared\n  owner. The two-publisher `tests/dedup.rs` assertions and the floor unit tests must stay green\n  byte-for-byte in semantics after the move — that is the guardrail.\n- **The public feed leads only on a genuine gap.** Correctness of the backstop rests on the edge\n  publishers reliably opening each `source_ts` tick first (sub-ms vs. tens of ms). If public ever\n  beats the edge for a tick (e.g. a brief edge hiccup), public leads that one tick and edge's later\n  same-`source_ts` samples are dropped as non-leader — acceptable (still fresh, single-source-coherent\n  within the tick), and self-corrects at the next tick. Worth a sentence in the PR.\n- **Recovery after a gap.** During a gap the public feed advances `high_water` to `T_public`. When the\n  edge resumes, its frames with `source_ts < T_public` are dropped as stale until edge catches past\n  `T_public`. Because `source_ts` is the shared venue block time, edge catches up within a tick or two\n  — correct (never regress to older edge data). Note it; do not special-case it.\n- **Shared mutable state across tasks.** The arbiter is on the emit path of every receiver and the\n  feeder; tasks now contend on one `Mutex` instead of each owning private state. Keep the critical\n  section tiny (the admit decision + send) and `emit` panic-free (no `unwrap` on feed data) so a panic\n  can't poison the lock. The single-receiver common path stays uncontended.\n- **Public-feed failure isolation.** Reconnect storms / decode errors must never block multicast. The\n  feeder is a separate task; failures back off and retry, never propagate.\n- **Instrument-definition availability.** A public quote needs its `(venue, symbol)` instrument in the\n  snapshot to satisfy precision-before-price. We rely on edge refdata being healthy while mktdata\n  stalls (the realistic backstop). Document the assumption + the standalone-public limitation.\n- **Unbounded public lag.** A long public reconnect can deliver very stale `source_ts`, which the floor\n  rejects (`< high_water`) — correct in steady state, but a public copy that is *both* stale and\n  arrives during an edge gap could be dropped. This is the window/lag failure mode the issue defers to\n  **#30** (window sizing); call it out, do not solve it here.\n- **TLS dependency surface.** Pick the `rustls`/webpki-roots feature (no system OpenSSL) for portable\n  container builds.\n- **HL subscription/connection limits.** Verify the documented per-connection subscription cap and\n  fan-out within one connection; log if the configured coin set would exceed it.\n\n## Testing strategy\n\n- `cargo test` — existing codec round-trips, refdata state machine, and the two-publisher\n  latch-to-leader tests (`tests/dedup.rs`) stay green after the floor/trade-dedup move to the arbiter.\n- Arbiter unit tests (migrated from the processor + primitives): leader latch within a tick, non-leader\n  drop, stale-tick drop for any publisher, new-tick re-latch, per-`(venue, symbol)` independence, and a\n  **`Publisher::PublicWs` loses to `Publisher::Edge` at the same tick** case (the steady-state backstop\n  in miniature); trade `trade_id` windowed dedup unchanged.\n- New E2E (`tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs`): drive the release binary with both the multicast replayer\n  and the mock WS input driver; assert `no_business_duplicates` + `source_ts` non-decreasing for the\n  steady-state case, and public emission for the edge-gap case.\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets` and `cargo fmt` clean.\n\n## Estimated scope (single PR)\n\n| Stage | Area | Est. lines added (code, non-test/doc) |\n|------|------|------------------------|\n| A | lift floor + trade dedup into shared arbiter + `Publisher` enum | ~120–150 |\n| B | WS feeder (parse-to-`f64`, no rescale) + TLS + wiring | ~180–210 |\n| C | harness + E2E | ~0–20 code (mostly tests) |\n| **Total** | | **~300–380** |\n\nComfortably under the 500-line threshold — ships as **one PR** with three internal commits (A → B → C)\nfor review legibility, per work-fast mode. #8 closes with it. (Lower than rev. 1: the floor already\nexists and the canonical-exponent rescale is gone.)\n\n## Open questions (defaults assumed; operator can override at re-review)\n\n1. **Content identity** — resolved to a default: under latch-to-leader, content is only ever compared\n   within one publisher's own stream, so the public feed needs **no** bit-compatible content and **no**\n   canonical-exponent rescale. The feeder parses px/sz to real-unit `f64`s and lets the floor's\n   publisher-leadership decide every cross-source race. Override only if you need the live bridge and\n   the offline `hl-bbo-feed-race` board to dedup on a byte-identical key now (separate follow-up).\n2. **Publisher identity type** — assumed a small `enum Publisher { Edge(IpAddr), PublicWs }` for the\n   floor's `P`, leaving the multicast `SeqTracker` keyed on `IpAddr` as today. Override if you'd rather\n   give the public feed a sentinel `IpAddr` and keep `P = IpAddr` (smaller diff, less self-documenting).\n3. **Shared arbiter vs. share-only-the-floor** — assumed the clean shared `Arbiter` emit stage (admit +\n   send in one place). The lighter alternative is to inject just the `Arc<Mutex<StalenessFloor>>` +\n   `Arc<Mutex<WindowedDedup>>` into both `TobProcessor` and the feeder and keep the `ctx.tx.send` call\n   sites. The arbiter is cleaner and centralizes the emit decision; flag if you prefer the minimal\n   injection.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":252,"newStart":1,"newLines":281,"lines":[" # Work Plan — Issue #8: Phase 3 WebSocket input feeder for public-API arbitrage"," "," > Roadbike planning artifact. Not committed (git-excluded via `.git/info/exclude`).","-> **Revision 1** — addresses operator feedback: (a) the quote dedup is a **floor**, not a","-> strict high-watermark; (b) the work is **one PR** (under the 500-line threshold, work-fast mode).","+> **Revision 2** — rewritten against the **updated base PR #29** (head `de61ad5`), which replaced the","+> strict watermark with a **latch-to-leader floor** (`StalenessFloor<K, V, P>`) keyed on a publisher","+> `P`. Operator steer: the public HL feed becomes **just another publisher racing for each slot** in","+> that existing floor — no new dedup primitive, and the content-identity question is now moot (see","+> \"The content-identity question, resolved\")."," "," ## Summary"," ","-Add the Hyperliquid **public** BBO/trades feed (`wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws`) as a second","-ingest source that emits the same `FeedMessage`s into the same broadcast channel as the DZ Edge","-multicast pipeline, so it acts as a **backstop**: the edge feed wins essentially always, and the","-public copy only surfaces when the edge feed gaps, stalls, or dies. Both copies of the same update","-share one canonical identity — the public block time normalizes to the *same* `source_ts_ns` as the","-edge copy — so a single shared deduper placed just before the broadcast collapses cross-source","-duplicates with no health check: first-arrival of a given update wins, the mirror copy is a pure","-no-op, and an edge gap lets the public copy through. The opening move is a refactor: relocate the","-deduper from inside `TobProcessor` to a shared pre-broadcast **arbiter** both the multicast","-processors and the new WS feeder converge on. The WebSocket **output** contract (PROTOCOL.md) is","-unchanged.","+Add the Hyperliquid **public** BBO/trades feed (`wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws`) as a second ingest","+source that emits the same `FeedMessage`s into the same broadcast channel as the DZ Edge multicast","+pipeline. PR #29 already turned the quote path into a **per-`(venue, symbol)` latch-to-leader floor**:","+within one `source_ts` tick, only the *leader* publisher (the first to open that tick) is emitted and","+every other publisher's sample at that tick is dropped; the leader is re-selected each new tick. The","+edge multicast publishers already race through this floor by source IP."," ","-## What changed in this revision","+The whole of this issue is therefore: **make the public WS feed one more publisher in that same","+floor.** Because the edge publishers deliver each `source_ts` tick with sub-millisecond delay and the","+public feed arrives tens of milliseconds later over the internet, an edge publisher essentially always","+opens (leads) each tick, so the public copy at that tick is dropped as a non-leader. When the edge","+feed gaps or stalls, no edge publisher opens the next tick, so the public feed's sample is the first to","+cross the floor (`source_ts > high_water`) — it leads and fills in. That is the backstop, and it falls","+out of the existing floor with **no health check and no content matching**. The WebSocket **output**","+contract (PROTOCOL.md) is unchanged."," ","-1. **Dedup is a floor, not a strict watermark.** Revision 0 was written against HEAD (`6fc5463`),","-   whose quote dedup is a strict-`>` `Watermark` (`admit iff source_ts > last`). That primitive has","-   a real regression for a full-state feed: it blanket-drops a **distinct** quote that happens to","-   carry the *same* `source_ts` as the previous one (same-ms/same-ns granularity is common), i.e. it","-   loses a legitimate update, not just a duplicate. The operator's steer is to make the quote dedup","-   a **staleness floor + content identity** instead (see \"Design: the floor\" below). This revision","-   rebuilds the plan around the floor and makes the BBO **content identity load-bearing** rather than","-   the deferred/optional path it was in revision 0.","-   - *Status note for re-review:* HEAD's `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` still ships the strict-`>`","-     `Watermark`; there is no `floor` in the tree yet. I am treating \"floor rather than watermark\" as","-     the **intended primitive to implement in this PR** (the floor *replaces* the watermark — see the","-     migration note in Stage A). If a floor implementation already exists somewhere I haven't seen,","-     the only change is \"reuse it\" instead of \"write it\"; the rest of the plan is unaffected.","-2. **One PR.** Revision 0 split the work into three stacked sub-issues because the full-content path","-   pushed the estimate to ~450–530. Re-scoped (lean stable content identity, **no** FNV","-   bit-compatibility with the offline board — deferred), the total lands under 500 and, in work-fast","-   mode, ships as a **single PR with three internal commits/stages** (A → B → C below) so each stage","-   is still independently reviewable in the diff. #8 closes with this PR.","+The one structural change: PR #29's floor lives **inside `TobProcessor`**, and there is one processor","+per multicast feed. For the public feed to race in the *same* floor as the edge HL feed (so their","+copies collapse instead of both reaching the WS as duplicates), the floor — and the trade","+`WindowedDedup` — must be **lifted into a process-wide shared arbiter** that both the multicast","+processors and the WS feeder funnel through. That refactor is Stage A."," ","-## Key context discovered during planning","+## Base-PR status / rebase note"," ","-- **Current dedup wiring.** `TobProcessor` (`src/ingest/processor.rs`) owns both deduper instances:","-  `quote_dedup: Watermark<(String, String)>` keyed `(venue, symbol)` on `source_ts`, and","-  `trade_dedup: WindowedDedup<(String, String), u64>` keyed on `trade_id`. Emission calls","-  `ctx.tx.send(...)` directly. There is one processor per feed (HL TOB, Phoenix TOB), each with its","-  *own* private dedup state — nothing is shared across transports yet. The `Watermark`/`WindowedDedup`","-  primitives already live in `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` (but the module is just primitives today, not a","-  shared emit stage).","-- **The floor fixes a known full-state regression.** Commit `27b6211` deduped quotes on a windowed","-  `(source_ts, content)` identity; `6fc5463` replaced it with the strict-`>` watermark, which is","-  simpler but drops distinct same-`source_ts` updates. The floor design below is essentially","-  `27b6211`'s `(source_ts, content)` identity **bounded by a staleness floor** (so memory stays","-  bounded and clearly-stale samples are rejected) — it gets the best of both: no full-state data loss,","-  still collapses cross-source mirror copies, still rejects stale laggards.","-- **Equal `source_ts` across transports is the dedup hinge.** The issue confirms","-  `edge.source_ts_ns == public.time_ms × 1_000_000` for the same update. So the edge and public copies","-  of one update land at the **same floor level (equal `source_ts`)**, where the content check","-  collapses them. For this to work, the public px/sz (decimal strings) must rescale to the **same","-  canonical exponents** the edge codec produces, so the two normalized BBO tuples are bit-equal. That","-  per-coin `szDecimals`/px rescale is therefore **load-bearing for dedup**, not just for emission.","-- **The TOB Quote frame already carries Bid/Ask Source Count.** The 60-byte Quote body pins","-  `bid source count` / `ask source count` at body offsets `+48` / `+50` in `codec.rs` (written as","-  zeros today). We do **not** need them for the floor — the content identity is the normalized BBO","-  tuple `(bid_px, bid_sz, ask_px, ask_sz)`, which the codec already decodes. (Decoding the source","-  counts is only needed for FNV bit-compat with the offline board, which is deferred.)","-- **`tokio-tungstenite = \"0.29\"` has no TLS feature enabled.** The outbound `wss://` client needs a","-  TLS feature in `Cargo.toml` (issue explicitly allows TLS in the container).","+My branch (`bdz/doublezero-edge-connect-8`) is currently tipped at the **old** PR #29 design","+(`6fc5463`, \"freshest-wins source_ts watermark\"). PR #29 has since been force-updated to the","+**latch-to-leader** design (`de61ad5`). **This work rebases onto the new PR #29 head**; the strict","+`Watermark` no longer exists in the tree and there is nothing to remove — the floor already ships.","+The arbiter primitives (`StalenessFloor`, `WindowedDedup`) live in `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` today as","+plain primitives owned by `TobProcessor`; Stage A promotes them to a shared emit stage. #8 closes with","+this single PR."," ","-## Design: the floor (replaces the strict watermark)","+## What changed since revision 1"," ","-Quote dedup becomes a per-`(venue, symbol)` **floor + content identity**, keyed `(venue, symbol)`:","+Revision 1 was written against the *watermark* PR #29 and invented a \"staleness floor + content","+identity\" primitive plus an elaborate \"rescale public px/sz to the edge's canonical exponents so the","+two BBO tuples are bit-equal\" requirement, because under a content-keyed merge the public and edge","+copies had to hash identically to collapse. **All of that is now deleted.** Under latch-to-leader:"," ","-- Keep `floor` = the highest `source_ts` admitted for the key, plus the small set of **content","-  identities** admitted *at* that `source_ts` (the normalized BBO tuple, or a cheap stable hash of it).","-- `source_ts < floor` → **reject** (stale: the market has moved on; a lagging publisher's old sample).","-- `source_ts > floor` → **admit**, advance the floor, reset the content set to this one identity.","-- `source_ts == floor` → **admit iff** the content identity is not already in the set (a genuinely","-  *distinct* same-instant update is kept — the regression the strict watermark introduced); a competing","-  publisher's **identical** mirror copy has the same identity → already present → **dropped**.","+- The floor **already exists** (`StalenessFloor`) — I reuse it, I do not write a new primitive.","+- Cross-source dedup is decided by **publisher leadership per tick**, never by content. So the public","+  feed's px/sz do **not** need to match the edge's bit-for-bit, the canonical-exponent rescale is","+  gone, and the FNV/`StableBBOHash` bit-compat discussion is irrelevant (not deferred — moot).","+- The public feeder shrinks accordingly: it parses HL decimal strings straight to real-unit `f64`s","+  (the same units `apply_exponent` produces on the edge side) and emits."," ","-Why this satisfies the backstop with no health check:","-- *Steady state* — edge emits `T` (floor=`T`, set={edge-content}); the public mirror arrives later","-  with `source_ts==T` and identical content → present → dropped. ✓","-- *Edge gap* — edge stalls at `T`; public emits `T+1, T+2, …`, each `> floor` → admitted. ✓","-- *Recovery / equal race* — whichever transport delivers a given `source_ts` first sets the floor +","-  content; the other's identical copy is dropped; a *distinct* same-`source_ts` update still gets","-  through. ✓","+## The content-identity question, resolved"," ","-Bound & memory: the content set is per-key and only holds identities at the *current* floor level, so","-it resets every time the floor advances — bounded by the count of distinct same-`source_ts` updates,","-which is tiny. (Trades are unaffected: they keep `WindowedDedup` on `trade_id` — a trade is a","-point-in-time event, not state, so a floor would lose prints.)","+The operator asked for a clearer explanation or a good default on content identity. Here it is, then","+the choice:"," ","-**Content identity scope (lean, on purpose).** The identity is the bridge's own normalized BBO tuple,","-hashed with any stable hasher — it does **not** need to be bit-compatible with the offline","-`hl-bbo-feed-race` board's `StableBBOHash` (FNV-1a64 over rescaled-per-coin fields). Bit-compat with","-the offline board is **explicitly deferred** (it would add the `bid_n`/`ask_n` codec decode + an","-FNV-1a64 matching the board byte-for-byte, ~80–100 lines and a deliberate oracle change) and is *not*","-required for the bridge's correctness or the acceptance criteria. If the operator later needs the live","-bridge and offline analytics to dedup on a bit-identical key, that is a small follow-up issue.","+Trace `StalenessFloor::admit(key, source_ts, content, publisher)` for a tick that is already open","+(`source_ts == high_water`):"," ","-## Approach (single PR, three internal stages A → B → C)","+- if `publisher != leader` → **dropped immediately; `content` is never looked at.**","+- if `publisher == leader` → admit iff `content` is new **in the leader's own set** (drops that one","+  publisher's exact repeats)."," ","-**A. Shared pre-broadcast arbiter + the floor (the core refactor).**","-Promote `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` from \"primitives\" to a shared emit stage. Add an `Arbiter` that owns","-the `broadcast::Sender<FeedMessage>` plus the dedup state — the new `Floor` for quotes (keyed","-`(venue, symbol)`, holding `source_ts` + the content-identity set) and the existing `WindowedDedup`","-for trades — and exposes a single `emit(FeedMessage)` entry point: it applies the floor to `Quote`,","-the windowed dedup to `Trade`, and passes `Instrument`/`Depth`/`Midpoint`/`Status` straight through.","-Wrap it as `Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>` (`SharedArbiter`) so every multicast receiver task **and** the new","-WS feeder funnel through one instance per process. `FrameCtx` swaps its raw `tx: &broadcast::Sender`","-for an emit path into the arbiter; `TobProcessor` loses `quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup` (and","-`admit_quote`/`admit_trade`) and calls `ctx.emit(...)`. The WS sink keeps `tx.subscribe()` exactly as","-today (the arbiter exposes the `Sender`). The strict `Watermark` is **removed** and its three quote","-unit tests are migrated to the floor's semantics (now including the \"distinct same-`source_ts` update","-is *kept*\" case the watermark failed).","+So `content` is only ever compared **within a single publisher's own stream**. Two different","+publishers' contents are *never* compared to each other — the non-leader loses on identity before","+content is consulted. Therefore the public feed's content does **not** need to equal the edge feed's","+content for the same update; there is nothing to make bit-compatible."," ","+**Choice (default, operator can override):** drop the cross-source content-matching requirement and","+the canonical-exponent rescale entirely. The public feeder computes content the same uniform way every","+quote does (over the normalized BBO `f64`s), purely so the floor can drop the public feed's *own*","+exact repeats when the public feed happens to be the leader (during an edge gap). px/sz are parsed to","+real-unit `f64`s directly. *If* a future requirement needs the live bridge and the offline","+`hl-bbo-feed-race` board to dedup on a byte-identical key, that is a separate follow-up; it is not","+needed for this issue's correctness or acceptance criteria.","+","+## Key context discovered during planning (against `de61ad5`)","+","+- **Floor + send live in `TobProcessor`.** `src/ingest/processor.rs`:","+  `quote_dedup: StalenessFloor<(String, String), QuoteContent, IpAddr>` and","+  `trade_dedup: WindowedDedup<(String, String), u64>`. Emission is","+  `if self.admit_quote(...) { ctx.tx.send(FeedMessage::Quote(quote)) }` (and the trade analog). There","+  is **one processor per feed**, so today each feed has its own private floor — fine for the edge's","+  two source-IP publishers (same processor, same group), but the public WS feed is a *separate task*","+  and would have a *separate* floor unless we share it.","+- **`FrameCtx`** (`src/ingest/receiver.rs:81`) carries `tx: &broadcast::Sender<FeedMessage>`,","+  `instruments: &InstrumentSnapshot`, and `publisher: IpAddr` (the datagram source IP — the existing","+  per-publisher demux key). `drive()`/`run_feed()` thread these in; `emit_status` sends straight on","+  `tx`.","+- **`publisher: P` is the floor's leader identity.** Today `P = IpAddr`. The public feed has no","+  multicast source IP, so the shared floor's `P` becomes a small `Publisher` enum","+  (`Edge(IpAddr)` | `PublicWs`) — the edge path wraps `ctx.publisher`, the feeder uses `PublicWs`.","+- **Units already line up.** Edge quotes are real-unit `f64`s via `apply_exponent(raw, exponent)`;","+  HL public px/sz are decimal strings in real units. `\"104783.0\".parse::<f64>()` lands in the same","+  unit space, so when the public feed leads during a gap, consumers see consistent magnitudes — no","+  rescale needed.","+- **Precision-before-price for the public feed** comes from the shared `InstrumentSnapshot`","+  (`Mutex<HashMap>` keyed `(venue, symbol)`), which the edge refdata populates. The feeder gates each","+  public quote on the `(venue, symbol)` instrument being present in that snapshot — the realistic","+  backstop scenario is edge **refdata healthy while mktdata stalls**. Standalone-public (no edge","+  refdata ever) is a documented limitation, deferred.","+- **TLS for the outbound client.** `tokio-tungstenite = \"0.29\"` is present (used as a WS *server* by","+  the sink, no TLS feature). The `wss://` *client* needs a `rustls`-based feature enabled in","+  `Cargo.toml` (confirm the exact 0.29 feature name during implementation; pick the webpki-roots","+  variant for a portable container with no system OpenSSL).","+","+## Approach (single PR, three internal commits A → B → C)","+","+**A. Lift the floor + trade dedup into a shared pre-broadcast arbiter (the core refactor).**","+Promote `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` from \"primitives owned by the processor\" to a shared emit stage. Add","+an `Arbiter` that owns the `broadcast::Sender<FeedMessage>` **plus** the dedup state — the existing","+`StalenessFloor` for quotes (keyed `(venue, symbol)`, `P = Publisher`) and the existing `WindowedDedup`","+for trades — and exposes one entry point `emit(msg, publisher)`: it applies the floor to `Quote`","+(computing the content identity over the normalized BBO `f64`s), the windowed dedup to `Trade` (on","+`trade_id`), and passes `Instrument`/`Depth`/`Midpoint`/`Status` straight through. Wrap it","+`Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>` (`SharedArbiter`) so every multicast receiver task **and** the new WS feeder","+funnel through one instance per process — one floor per `(venue, symbol)`, so the edge HL processor and","+the public feeder converge on the *same* floor and race. Introduce the `Publisher` enum. `FrameCtx`","+swaps its raw `tx` for the arbiter handle (or an `emit` path); `TobProcessor` loses","+`quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup`/`admit_quote`/`admit_trade`/`QuoteContent` and calls `ctx.emit(...)`,","+wrapping `ctx.publisher` as `Publisher::Edge(ip)`. `emit_status` routes through the arbiter","+passthrough. The WS sink keeps `tx.subscribe()` unchanged (the arbiter exposes the `Sender`). The","+`StalenessFloor`/`WindowedDedup` unit tests move with the primitives; the content-identity unit (raw","+`QuoteContent`) becomes a content-over-normalized-`f64`s unit. **No behavior change to the edge path**","+— this is a relocation; the latch-to-leader semantics are identical.","+"," **B. WS-client feeder task (the new ingest source).**","-New ingest module `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` connects to `wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws` over TLS,","-sends one `{\"method\":\"subscribe\",\"subscription\":{\"type\":\"bbo\",\"coin\":\"<C>\"}}` (and `trades`) per","-carried coin over a **single shared connection** (HL has no wildcard), decodes the HL JSON","-`bbo`/`trades` into `FeedMessage::Quote`/`Trade` (venue `\"Hyperliquid\"`, public `time` ms →","-`source_ts_ns`, `tid` → `trade_id`), **rescales px/sz to the edge's canonical exponents so the content","-identity matches across transports**, and emits into the shared arbiter. It runs as its own","-`tokio::spawn`ed task with **reconnect + exponential backoff**; all decode/socket errors are swallowed","-(logged) so the multicast hot path is never affected. **Off by default**, gated on a non-empty config","-value per the repo's source/sink activation convention. A `--ws-input-url` override lets the harness","-point it at a local mock.","+New module `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` connects to `wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws` over TLS, sends one","+`{\"method\":\"subscribe\",\"subscription\":{\"type\":\"bbo\",\"coin\":\"<C>\"}}` and one `trades` subscription per","+carried coin over a **single shared connection** (HL has no wildcard; check the documented","+per-connection subscription cap and log if the configured coin set would exceed it), decodes HL","+`bbo`/`trades` JSON into `FeedMessage::Quote`/`Trade` (venue `\"Hyperliquid\"`, public block `time` ms →","+`source_ts_ns = time * 1_000_000` so it shares the **same canonical `source_ts`** as the edge copy —","+this is what puts both copies in the *same* floor tick; `tid` → `trade_id`), parses px/sz decimal","+strings to real-unit `f64`s, **gates on the `(venue, symbol)` instrument being present in the shared","+`InstrumentSnapshot`** (precision before price), and calls `arbiter.emit(msg, Publisher::PublicWs)`.","+It runs as its own `tokio::spawn`ed task with **reconnect + exponential backoff**; all decode/socket","+errors are swallowed (logged) so the multicast hot path is never touched. **Off by default**, gated on","+a non-empty config value per the repo's source/sink activation convention. A `--ws-input-url` override","+points the feeder at a local mock for the E2E."," "," **C. Mock-WS input harness + backstop E2E (mostly tests).**"," A tiny in-test HL WS server / scripted driver (`tests/common/ws_input.rs`) that plays scripted"," `bbo`/`trades` JSON; reuse `ws_client` + `assertions` unchanged on the output side. Two E2E cases:","-**edge-wins-in-steady-state** (edge + public both fed; public copies dropped as no-ops;","-`no_business_duplicates` green) and **edge-gap → public fills in** (edge mktdata withheld; public","-copies emitted).","+**edge-leads-in-steady-state** (edge + public both fed the same `source_ts` ticks; public dropped as a","+non-leader; `no_business_duplicates` green, `source_ts` non-decreasing) and **edge-gap → public leads**","+(edge mktdata withheld; public opens the new ticks and is emitted)."," "," ## Files to change / create"," ","-### Stage A — shared arbiter + floor (refactor; behavior change is *intentional and tested*: floor, not watermark)","-- `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` — replace `Watermark` with `Floor` (per-key `source_ts` + content-identity","-  set; `admit(key, source_ts, content_id) -> bool`). Add `Arbiter` (owns `broadcast::Sender` + `Floor`","-  + `WindowedDedup`) and `emit(FeedMessage)`. Define `SharedArbiter = Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>`. Migrate the","-  three quote unit tests to floor semantics (add the \"distinct same-`source_ts` admitted\" case).","-  *(~80–110 lines net.)*","-- `src/ingest/receiver.rs` — `FrameCtx` carries the arbiter/emit path instead of a raw `tx`;","-  `drive()`/`run_feed()` thread it through; `emit_status` routes through the arbiter. *(~30 lines.)*","-- `src/ingest/processor.rs` — drop `quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup`/`admit_quote`/`admit_trade` from","-  `TobProcessor`; compute the quote content identity at emit; replace every `ctx.tx.send(...)` with","-  `ctx.emit(...)`. `MidpointProcessor`/`MboProcessor` emit through `ctx` too. Migrate the in-processor","-  dedup unit tests to the arbiter/floor. *(~40 lines changed, net reduction.)*","-- `src/main.rs` — build `SharedArbiter` from the broadcast `Sender`; pass it to each receiver; the WS","-  sink still gets `tx.subscribe()`. *(~10 lines.)*","-- `tests/dedup.rs` — re-target the freshest-wins / per-`(venue,symbol)`-independence assertions to the","-  floor + arbiter; add a distinct-same-`source_ts` case. *(tests, excluded from count.)*","+### Stage A — shared arbiter (refactor; **behavior-preserving** for the edge path)","+- `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` — add `pub enum Publisher { Edge(IpAddr), PublicWs }`; switch the","+  `StalenessFloor`'s `P` at the call sites to `Publisher` (the primitive is already generic over","+  `P: Eq`). Add `struct Arbiter { tx, quotes: StalenessFloor<(String,String), QuoteId, Publisher>,","+  trades: WindowedDedup<(String,String), u64> }` with `emit(&mut self, msg, publisher)` and a","+  `sender()` accessor; `type SharedArbiter = Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>`. Define `QuoteId` as a stable hash /","+  bit-tuple over the normalized BBO `f64`s. Keep all existing floor/windowed unit tests; migrate the","+  content unit to `QuoteId`. *(~90–120 lines net.)*","+- `src/ingest/receiver.rs` — `FrameCtx` carries the arbiter handle (or an `emit` path) instead of a","+  raw `tx`; `drive()`/`run_feed()` thread `SharedArbiter` through; `emit_status` routes through the","+  arbiter passthrough. *(~30 lines.)*","+- `src/ingest/processor.rs` — drop `quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup`/`admit_quote`/`admit_trade` and the raw","+  `QuoteContent` from `TobProcessor`; replace `if self.admit_quote(...) { ctx.tx.send(...) }` with","+  `ctx.emit(FeedMessage::Quote(quote), Publisher::Edge(ctx.publisher))` (trade analog).","+  `MidpointProcessor`/`MboProcessor` emit through `ctx` too (passthrough). Move the in-processor dedup","+  unit tests to the arbiter. *(~40 lines changed, net reduction.)*","+- `src/main.rs` — build `SharedArbiter` around the broadcast `Sender`; pass it to each receiver; the","+  WS sink still gets `tx.subscribe()` via `arbiter.sender()`. *(~10 lines.)*","+- `tests/dedup.rs` — re-target the existing two-publisher latch-to-leader assertions to the shared","+  arbiter (semantics unchanged; only the owner moved). *(tests, excluded from count.)*"," "," ### Stage B — WS feeder + TLS + wiring (the new ingest source)","-- `Cargo.toml` — enable a `rustls`-based `tokio-tungstenite` TLS feature (no system OpenSSL, portable","-  container build); confirm the exact 0.29 feature name during implementation. *(deps.)*","+- `Cargo.toml` — enable a `rustls`-based `tokio-tungstenite` TLS feature (webpki-roots; no system","+  OpenSSL); confirm the exact 0.29 feature name during implementation. *(deps.)*"," - `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` (new) — HL JSON structs (`bbo`, `trades`), single-connection connect +","-  per-coin subscribe fan-out (with a check against HL's documented subscription/connection limits,","-  logged if exceeded), decode → `FeedMessage`, public `time` ms → `source_ts_ns`, **px/sz rescale to","-  canonical exponents** (so content identity matches the edge), reconnect/backoff, error isolation,","-  emit into the shared arbiter, `--ws-input-url` override. *(~190–220 lines.)*","+  per-coin subscribe fan-out (log if the coin set exceeds HL's documented subscription cap), decode →","+  `FeedMessage`, public `time` ms → `source_ts_ns`, decimal-string px/sz → real-unit `f64`,","+  `(venue, symbol)` instrument-presence gate against the shared `InstrumentSnapshot`,","+  reconnect/backoff, error isolation, `emit(msg, Publisher::PublicWs)`, `--ws-input-url` override.","+  *(~150–180 lines — smaller than rev. 1, no rescale machinery.)*"," - `src/ingest/mod.rs` — `pub mod ws_feeder;`. *(1 line.)*"," - `src/main.rs` — `--ws-input-coins` / `--ws-input-url` flags (+ env `WS_INPUT_COINS`/`WS_INPUT_URL`),","-  spawn the feeder when enabled, include it in the `select!`/`JoinSet` lifecycle. *(~30 lines.)*","+  spawn the feeder when the coin list is non-empty, include it in the `select!`/`JoinSet` lifecycle.","+  *(~30 lines.)*"," "," ### Stage C — mock-WS input harness + backstop E2E (mostly tests)"," - `tests/common/ws_input.rs` (new) + `tests/common/mod.rs` — mock HL WS server / scripted driver.","   *(tests, excluded.)*","-- `tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs` (new) — edge-wins-in-steady-state + edge-gap→public-fills.","+- `tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs` (new) — edge-leads-in-steady-state + edge-gap→public-leads.","   *(tests, excluded.)*"," "," ### Docs (excluded from line count)"," - `README.md` — new **input source** subsection + flag/env row for the WS feeder (distinct from the","-  output-sink table); off by default, backstop semantics.","-- `CHANGELOG.md` — `[Unreleased] / Added` (WS feeder) and `Changed` (quote dedup: floor + content","-  identity, replacing the strict watermark) entries.","-- `CLAUDE.md` — document the shared arbiter stage, the floor primitive (replacing the watermark line),","-  the `ws_feeder` module, and that ingest now has two source transports (multicast + WS feeder)","-  converging on one arbiter; note PROTOCOL.md is unchanged.","+  output-sink table); off by default, backstop-by-racing semantics.","+- `CHANGELOG.md` — `[Unreleased] / Added` (public WS input feeder; shared arbiter emit stage).","+- `CLAUDE.md` — document the shared arbiter stage (floor + trade dedup lifted out of `TobProcessor`),","+  the `Publisher` enum, the `ws_feeder` module, and that ingest now has two source transports","+  (multicast + WS feeder) converging on one floor that races them per `(venue, symbol)` tick; note","+  PROTOCOL.md is unchanged."," - `PROTOCOL.md` — **no change** (output contract unchanged); state this explicitly in the PR."," "," ## Risks & considerations"," ","-- **Floor is an intentional behavior change (not behavior-preserving).** Unlike revision 0's","-  pure-relocation framing, swapping the strict watermark for the floor changes output: a distinct","-  same-`source_ts` quote is now **kept** where it was dropped. This is the *point* of the operator's","-  steer; it is covered by a new explicit unit test and the migrated `tests/dedup.rs` assertions, and","-  it does not affect the PROTOCOL.md surface (still full-state, self-healing).","-- **Content-identity match across transports.** Dedup of equal-`source_ts` mirror copies only works if","-  the public px/sz rescale produces the *same* normalized tuple as the edge codec. A rescale mismatch","-  would let a duplicate through. Mitigation: unit-test the rescale against known edge-decoded values","-  for the carried coins; the E2E `no_business_duplicates` oracle catches any residual drift.","+- **Refactor is behavior-preserving for the edge path** (unlike rev. 1, which changed dedup","+  semantics). Stage A only relocates the existing latch-to-leader floor and trade dedup into a shared","+  owner. The two-publisher `tests/dedup.rs` assertions and the floor unit tests must stay green","+  byte-for-byte in semantics after the move — that is the guardrail.","+- **The public feed leads only on a genuine gap.** Correctness of the backstop rests on the edge","+  publishers reliably opening each `source_ts` tick first (sub-ms vs. tens of ms). If public ever","+  beats the edge for a tick (e.g. a brief edge hiccup), public leads that one tick and edge's later","+  same-`source_ts` samples are dropped as non-leader — acceptable (still fresh, single-source-coherent","+  within the tick), and self-corrects at the next tick. Worth a sentence in the PR.","+- **Recovery after a gap.** During a gap the public feed advances `high_water` to `T_public`. When the","+  edge resumes, its frames with `source_ts < T_public` are dropped as stale until edge catches past","+  `T_public`. Because `source_ts` is the shared venue block time, edge catches up within a tick or two","+  — correct (never regress to older edge data). Note it; do not special-case it."," - **Shared mutable state across tasks.** The arbiter is on the emit path of every receiver and the","-  feeder; multiple tasks now contend on one `Mutex` instead of each owning private state. Keep the","-  critical section tiny (the floor/dedup decision only) and `emit` panic-free (no `unwrap` on user","-  data) so a panic can't poison the lock. Existing single-feed throughput is unaffected (lock is","-  uncontended in the common single-receiver path).","+  feeder; tasks now contend on one `Mutex` instead of each owning private state. Keep the critical","+  section tiny (the admit decision + send) and `emit` panic-free (no `unwrap` on feed data) so a panic","+  can't poison the lock. The single-receiver common path stays uncontended."," - **Public-feed failure isolation.** Reconnect storms / decode errors must never block multicast. The","   feeder is a separate task; failures back off and retry, never propagate.","-- **Unbounded public lag.** A long public reconnect can deliver very stale `source_ts`, which the","-  floor rejects (`< floor`) — correct for steady state, but a public copy that is *both* stale and","-  arrives during an edge gap could still be dropped. This is the window/lag failure mode the issue","-  explicitly defers to **#30** (window sizing); call it out, do not solve it here.","-- **Instrument definition availability.** A public quote needs its `(venue, symbol)` instrument already","-  in the snapshot to satisfy `instrument_before_price`. We rely on the edge feed's refdata being","-  healthy while its mktdata stalls (the realistic backstop scenario); document the assumption and the","-  standalone-public limitation.","-- **TLS dependency surface.** Pick the `rustls`-based feature (no system OpenSSL) for portable","+- **Instrument-definition availability.** A public quote needs its `(venue, symbol)` instrument in the","+  snapshot to satisfy precision-before-price. We rely on edge refdata being healthy while mktdata","+  stalls (the realistic backstop). Document the assumption + the standalone-public limitation.","+- **Unbounded public lag.** A long public reconnect can deliver very stale `source_ts`, which the floor","+  rejects (`< high_water`) — correct in steady state, but a public copy that is *both* stale and","+  arrives during an edge gap could be dropped. This is the window/lag failure mode the issue defers to","+  **#30** (window sizing); call it out, do not solve it here.","+- **TLS dependency surface.** Pick the `rustls`/webpki-roots feature (no system OpenSSL) for portable","   container builds."," - **HL subscription/connection limits.** Verify the documented per-connection subscription cap and","   fan-out within one connection; log if the configured coin set would exceed it."," "," ## Testing strategy"," ","-- `cargo test` — existing codec round-trips, refdata state machine, and the multi-publisher dedup","-  tests (`tests/dedup.rs`) stay green after migration to the floor + arbiter.","-- New arbiter/floor unit tests: stale-reject (`< floor`), advance (`> floor`), **distinct","-  same-`source_ts` admitted**, **identical same-`source_ts` dropped** (cross-source collapse),","-  per-`(venue, symbol)` independence; trade `trade_id` dedup unchanged.","+- `cargo test` — existing codec round-trips, refdata state machine, and the two-publisher","+  latch-to-leader tests (`tests/dedup.rs`) stay green after the floor/trade-dedup move to the arbiter.","+- Arbiter unit tests (migrated from the processor + primitives): leader latch within a tick, non-leader","+  drop, stale-tick drop for any publisher, new-tick re-latch, per-`(venue, symbol)` independence, and a","+  **`Publisher::PublicWs` loses to `Publisher::Edge` at the same tick** case (the steady-state backstop","+  in miniature); trade `trade_id` windowed dedup unchanged."," - New E2E (`tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs`): drive the release binary with both the multicast replayer","-  and the mock WS input driver; assert `no_business_duplicates` + the two backstop cases.","+  and the mock WS input driver; assert `no_business_duplicates` + `source_ts` non-decreasing for the","+  steady-state case, and public emission for the edge-gap case."," - `cargo clippy --all-targets` and `cargo fmt` clean."," "," ## Estimated scope (single PR)"," "," | Stage | Area | Est. lines added (code, non-test/doc) |"," |------|------|------------------------|","-| A | shared arbiter + floor refactor | ~120–160 |","-| B | WS feeder + px/sz rescale + TLS + wiring | ~230–260 |","+| A | lift floor + trade dedup into shared arbiter + `Publisher` enum | ~120–150 |","+| B | WS feeder (parse-to-`f64`, no rescale) + TLS + wiring | ~180–210 |"," | C | harness + E2E | ~0–20 code (mostly tests) |","-| **Total** | | **~350–440** |","+| **Total** | | **~300–380** |"," ","-Comfortably under the 500-line threshold, so per work-fast mode it ships as **one PR** with three","-internal commits (A → B → C) for review legibility. The deferred FNV/`StableBBOHash` bit-compat path","-(~80–100 lines + an oracle change) is **out of scope** for this PR.","+Comfortably under the 500-line threshold — ships as **one PR** with three internal commits (A → B → C)","+for review legibility, per work-fast mode. #8 closes with it. (Lower than rev. 1: the floor already","+exists and the canonical-exponent rescale is gone.)"," "," ## Open questions (defaults assumed; operator can override at re-review)"," ","-1. **Floor semantics** — assumed **staleness floor + bridge-local content identity** as specified in","-   \"Design: the floor\" (reject `< floor`; collapse identical at-`floor` copies; keep distinct","-   at-`floor` updates). I found **no existing `floor` in the tree** — HEAD still ships the strict-`>`","-   `Watermark` — so this PR *implements* the floor and removes the watermark. If a floor primitive","-   already exists elsewhere, the plan reuses it unchanged. **Confirm this matches the intended floor.**","-2. **Content identity = bit-compatible with the offline board?** Assumed **no** (lean, bridge-local","-   stable hash; FNV/`StableBBOHash` bit-compat deferred to a follow-up). Override if live-bridge ↔","-   offline-analytics bit-identical dedup is required now (+~80–100 lines, deliberate oracle change).","-3. **One PR vs. stacked** — assumed **one PR** (under 500, work-fast mode) with A → B → C as internal","-   commits; #8 closes with it.","+1. **Content identity** — resolved to a default: under latch-to-leader, content is only ever compared","+   within one publisher's own stream, so the public feed needs **no** bit-compatible content and **no**","+   canonical-exponent rescale. The feeder parses px/sz to real-unit `f64`s and lets the floor's","+   publisher-leadership decide every cross-source race. Override only if you need the live bridge and","+   the offline `hl-bbo-feed-race` board to dedup on a byte-identical key now (separate follow-up).","+2. **Publisher identity type** — assumed a small `enum Publisher { Edge(IpAddr), PublicWs }` for the","+   floor's `P`, leaving the multicast `SeqTracker` keyed on `IpAddr` as today. Override if you'd rather","+   give the public feed a sentinel `IpAddr` and keep `P = IpAddr` (smaller diff, less self-documenting).","+3. **Shared arbiter vs. share-only-the-floor** — assumed the clean shared `Arbiter` emit stage (admit +","+   send in one place). The lighter alternative is to inject just the `Arc<Mutex<StalenessFloor>>` +","+   `Arc<Mutex<WindowedDedup>>` into both `TobProcessor` and the feeder and keep the `ctx.tx.send` call","+   sites. The arbiter is cleaner and centralizes the emit decision; flag if you prefer the minimal","+   injection."]}],"originalFile":"# Work Plan — Issue #8: Phase 3 WebSocket input feeder for public-API arbitrage\n\n> Roadbike planning artifact. Not committed (git-excluded via `.git/info/exclude`).\n> **Revision 1** — addresses operator feedback: (a) the quote dedup is a **floor**, not a\n> strict high-watermark; (b) the work is **one PR** (under the 500-line threshold, work-fast mode).\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd the Hyperliquid **public** BBO/trades feed (`wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws`) as a second\ningest source that emits the same `FeedMessage`s into the same broadcast channel as the DZ Edge\nmulticast pipeline, so it acts as a **backstop**: the edge feed wins essentially always, and the\npublic copy only surfaces when the edge feed gaps, stalls, or dies. Both copies of the same update\nshare one canonical identity — the public block time normalizes to the *same* `source_ts_ns` as the\nedge copy — so a single shared deduper placed just before the broadcast collapses cross-source\nduplicates with no health check: first-arrival of a given update wins, the mirror copy is a pure\nno-op, and an edge gap lets the public copy through. The opening move is a refactor: relocate the\ndeduper from inside `TobProcessor` to a shared pre-broadcast **arbiter** both the multicast\nprocessors and the new WS feeder converge on. The WebSocket **output** contract (PROTOCOL.md) is\nunchanged.\n\n## What changed in this revision\n\n1. **Dedup is a floor, not a strict watermark.** Revision 0 was written against HEAD (`6fc5463`),\n   whose quote dedup is a strict-`>` `Watermark` (`admit iff source_ts > last`). That primitive has\n   a real regression for a full-state feed: it blanket-drops a **distinct** quote that happens to\n   carry the *same* `source_ts` as the previous one (same-ms/same-ns granularity is common), i.e. it\n   loses a legitimate update, not just a duplicate. The operator's steer is to make the quote dedup\n   a **staleness floor + content identity** instead (see \"Design: the floor\" below). This revision\n   rebuilds the plan around the floor and makes the BBO **content identity load-bearing** rather than\n   the deferred/optional path it was in revision 0.\n   - *Status note for re-review:* HEAD's `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` still ships the strict-`>`\n     `Watermark`; there is no `floor` in the tree yet. I am treating \"floor rather than watermark\" as\n     the **intended primitive to implement in this PR** (the floor *replaces* the watermark — see the\n     migration note in Stage A). If a floor implementation already exists somewhere I haven't seen,\n     the only change is \"reuse it\" instead of \"write it\"; the rest of the plan is unaffected.\n2. **One PR.** Revision 0 split the work into three stacked sub-issues because the full-content path\n   pushed the estimate to ~450–530. Re-scoped (lean stable content identity, **no** FNV\n   bit-compatibility with the offline board — deferred), the total lands under 500 and, in work-fast\n   mode, ships as a **single PR with three internal commits/stages** (A → B → C below) so each stage\n   is still independently reviewable in the diff. #8 closes with this PR.\n\n## Key context discovered during planning\n\n- **Current dedup wiring.** `TobProcessor` (`src/ingest/processor.rs`) owns both deduper instances:\n  `quote_dedup: Watermark<(String, String)>` keyed `(venue, symbol)` on `source_ts`, and\n  `trade_dedup: WindowedDedup<(String, String), u64>` keyed on `trade_id`. Emission calls\n  `ctx.tx.send(...)` directly. There is one processor per feed (HL TOB, Phoenix TOB), each with its\n  *own* private dedup state — nothing is shared across transports yet. The `Watermark`/`WindowedDedup`\n  primitives already live in `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` (but the module is just primitives today, not a\n  shared emit stage).\n- **The floor fixes a known full-state regression.** Commit `27b6211` deduped quotes on a windowed\n  `(source_ts, content)` identity; `6fc5463` replaced it with the strict-`>` watermark, which is\n  simpler but drops distinct same-`source_ts` updates. The floor design below is essentially\n  `27b6211`'s `(source_ts, content)` identity **bounded by a staleness floor** (so memory stays\n  bounded and clearly-stale samples are rejected) — it gets the best of both: no full-state data loss,\n  still collapses cross-source mirror copies, still rejects stale laggards.\n- **Equal `source_ts` across transports is the dedup hinge.** The issue confirms\n  `edge.source_ts_ns == public.time_ms × 1_000_000` for the same update. So the edge and public copies\n  of one update land at the **same floor level (equal `source_ts`)**, where the content check\n  collapses them. For this to work, the public px/sz (decimal strings) must rescale to the **same\n  canonical exponents** the edge codec produces, so the two normalized BBO tuples are bit-equal. That\n  per-coin `szDecimals`/px rescale is therefore **load-bearing for dedup**, not just for emission.\n- **The TOB Quote frame already carries Bid/Ask Source Count.** The 60-byte Quote body pins\n  `bid source count` / `ask source count` at body offsets `+48` / `+50` in `codec.rs` (written as\n  zeros today). We do **not** need them for the floor — the content identity is the normalized BBO\n  tuple `(bid_px, bid_sz, ask_px, ask_sz)`, which the codec already decodes. (Decoding the source\n  counts is only needed for FNV bit-compat with the offline board, which is deferred.)\n- **`tokio-tungstenite = \"0.29\"` has no TLS feature enabled.** The outbound `wss://` client needs a\n  TLS feature in `Cargo.toml` (issue explicitly allows TLS in the container).\n\n## Design: the floor (replaces the strict watermark)\n\nQuote dedup becomes a per-`(venue, symbol)` **floor + content identity**, keyed `(venue, symbol)`:\n\n- Keep `floor` = the highest `source_ts` admitted for the key, plus the small set of **content\n  identities** admitted *at* that `source_ts` (the normalized BBO tuple, or a cheap stable hash of it).\n- `source_ts < floor` → **reject** (stale: the market has moved on; a lagging publisher's old sample).\n- `source_ts > floor` → **admit**, advance the floor, reset the content set to this one identity.\n- `source_ts == floor` → **admit iff** the content identity is not already in the set (a genuinely\n  *distinct* same-instant update is kept — the regression the strict watermark introduced); a competing\n  publisher's **identical** mirror copy has the same identity → already present → **dropped**.\n\nWhy this satisfies the backstop with no health check:\n- *Steady state* — edge emits `T` (floor=`T`, set={edge-content}); the public mirror arrives later\n  with `source_ts==T` and identical content → present → dropped. ✓\n- *Edge gap* — edge stalls at `T`; public emits `T+1, T+2, …`, each `> floor` → admitted. ✓\n- *Recovery / equal race* — whichever transport delivers a given `source_ts` first sets the floor +\n  content; the other's identical copy is dropped; a *distinct* same-`source_ts` update still gets\n  through. ✓\n\nBound & memory: the content set is per-key and only holds identities at the *current* floor level, so\nit resets every time the floor advances — bounded by the count of distinct same-`source_ts` updates,\nwhich is tiny. (Trades are unaffected: they keep `WindowedDedup` on `trade_id` — a trade is a\npoint-in-time event, not state, so a floor would lose prints.)\n\n**Content identity scope (lean, on purpose).** The identity is the bridge's own normalized BBO tuple,\nhashed with any stable hasher — it does **not** need to be bit-compatible with the offline\n`hl-bbo-feed-race` board's `StableBBOHash` (FNV-1a64 over rescaled-per-coin fields). Bit-compat with\nthe offline board is **explicitly deferred** (it would add the `bid_n`/`ask_n` codec decode + an\nFNV-1a64 matching the board byte-for-byte, ~80–100 lines and a deliberate oracle change) and is *not*\nrequired for the bridge's correctness or the acceptance criteria. If the operator later needs the live\nbridge and offline analytics to dedup on a bit-identical key, that is a small follow-up issue.\n\n## Approach (single PR, three internal stages A → B → C)\n\n**A. Shared pre-broadcast arbiter + the floor (the core refactor).**\nPromote `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` from \"primitives\" to a shared emit stage. Add an `Arbiter` that owns\nthe `broadcast::Sender<FeedMessage>` plus the dedup state — the new `Floor` for quotes (keyed\n`(venue, symbol)`, holding `source_ts` + the content-identity set) and the existing `WindowedDedup`\nfor trades — and exposes a single `emit(FeedMessage)` entry point: it applies the floor to `Quote`,\nthe windowed dedup to `Trade`, and passes `Instrument`/`Depth`/`Midpoint`/`Status` straight through.\nWrap it as `Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>` (`SharedArbiter`) so every multicast receiver task **and** the new\nWS feeder funnel through one instance per process. `FrameCtx` swaps its raw `tx: &broadcast::Sender`\nfor an emit path into the arbiter; `TobProcessor` loses `quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup` (and\n`admit_quote`/`admit_trade`) and calls `ctx.emit(...)`. The WS sink keeps `tx.subscribe()` exactly as\ntoday (the arbiter exposes the `Sender`). The strict `Watermark` is **removed** and its three quote\nunit tests are migrated to the floor's semantics (now including the \"distinct same-`source_ts` update\nis *kept*\" case the watermark failed).\n\n**B. WS-client feeder task (the new ingest source).**\nNew ingest module `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` connects to `wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws` over TLS,\nsends one `{\"method\":\"subscribe\",\"subscription\":{\"type\":\"bbo\",\"coin\":\"<C>\"}}` (and `trades`) per\ncarried coin over a **single shared connection** (HL has no wildcard), decodes the HL JSON\n`bbo`/`trades` into `FeedMessage::Quote`/`Trade` (venue `\"Hyperliquid\"`, public `time` ms →\n`source_ts_ns`, `tid` → `trade_id`), **rescales px/sz to the edge's canonical exponents so the content\nidentity matches across transports**, and emits into the shared arbiter. It runs as its own\n`tokio::spawn`ed task with **reconnect + exponential backoff**; all decode/socket errors are swallowed\n(logged) so the multicast hot path is never affected. **Off by default**, gated on a non-empty config\nvalue per the repo's source/sink activation convention. A `--ws-input-url` override lets the harness\npoint it at a local mock.\n\n**C. Mock-WS input harness + backstop E2E (mostly tests).**\nA tiny in-test HL WS server / scripted driver (`tests/common/ws_input.rs`) that plays scripted\n`bbo`/`trades` JSON; reuse `ws_client` + `assertions` unchanged on the output side. Two E2E cases:\n**edge-wins-in-steady-state** (edge + public both fed; public copies dropped as no-ops;\n`no_business_duplicates` green) and **edge-gap → public fills in** (edge mktdata withheld; public\ncopies emitted).\n\n## Files to change / create\n\n### Stage A — shared arbiter + floor (refactor; behavior change is *intentional and tested*: floor, not watermark)\n- `src/ingest/arbiter.rs` — replace `Watermark` with `Floor` (per-key `source_ts` + content-identity\n  set; `admit(key, source_ts, content_id) -> bool`). Add `Arbiter` (owns `broadcast::Sender` + `Floor`\n  + `WindowedDedup`) and `emit(FeedMessage)`. Define `SharedArbiter = Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>`. Migrate the\n  three quote unit tests to floor semantics (add the \"distinct same-`source_ts` admitted\" case).\n  *(~80–110 lines net.)*\n- `src/ingest/receiver.rs` — `FrameCtx` carries the arbiter/emit path instead of a raw `tx`;\n  `drive()`/`run_feed()` thread it through; `emit_status` routes through the arbiter. *(~30 lines.)*\n- `src/ingest/processor.rs` — drop `quote_dedup`/`trade_dedup`/`admit_quote`/`admit_trade` from\n  `TobProcessor`; compute the quote content identity at emit; replace every `ctx.tx.send(...)` with\n  `ctx.emit(...)`. `MidpointProcessor`/`MboProcessor` emit through `ctx` too. Migrate the in-processor\n  dedup unit tests to the arbiter/floor. *(~40 lines changed, net reduction.)*\n- `src/main.rs` — build `SharedArbiter` from the broadcast `Sender`; pass it to each receiver; the WS\n  sink still gets `tx.subscribe()`. *(~10 lines.)*\n- `tests/dedup.rs` — re-target the freshest-wins / per-`(venue,symbol)`-independence assertions to the\n  floor + arbiter; add a distinct-same-`source_ts` case. *(tests, excluded from count.)*\n\n### Stage B — WS feeder + TLS + wiring (the new ingest source)\n- `Cargo.toml` — enable a `rustls`-based `tokio-tungstenite` TLS feature (no system OpenSSL, portable\n  container build); confirm the exact 0.29 feature name during implementation. *(deps.)*\n- `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` (new) — HL JSON structs (`bbo`, `trades`), single-connection connect +\n  per-coin subscribe fan-out (with a check against HL's documented subscription/connection limits,\n  logged if exceeded), decode → `FeedMessage`, public `time` ms → `source_ts_ns`, **px/sz rescale to\n  canonical exponents** (so content identity matches the edge), reconnect/backoff, error isolation,\n  emit into the shared arbiter, `--ws-input-url` override. *(~190–220 lines.)*\n- `src/ingest/mod.rs` — `pub mod ws_feeder;`. *(1 line.)*\n- `src/main.rs` — `--ws-input-coins` / `--ws-input-url` flags (+ env `WS_INPUT_COINS`/`WS_INPUT_URL`),\n  spawn the feeder when enabled, include it in the `select!`/`JoinSet` lifecycle. *(~30 lines.)*\n\n### Stage C — mock-WS input harness + backstop E2E (mostly tests)\n- `tests/common/ws_input.rs` (new) + `tests/common/mod.rs` — mock HL WS server / scripted driver.\n  *(tests, excluded.)*\n- `tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs` (new) — edge-wins-in-steady-state + edge-gap→public-fills.\n  *(tests, excluded.)*\n\n### Docs (excluded from line count)\n- `README.md` — new **input source** subsection + flag/env row for the WS feeder (distinct from the\n  output-sink table); off by default, backstop semantics.\n- `CHANGELOG.md` — `[Unreleased] / Added` (WS feeder) and `Changed` (quote dedup: floor + content\n  identity, replacing the strict watermark) entries.\n- `CLAUDE.md` — document the shared arbiter stage, the floor primitive (replacing the watermark line),\n  the `ws_feeder` module, and that ingest now has two source transports (multicast + WS feeder)\n  converging on one arbiter; note PROTOCOL.md is unchanged.\n- `PROTOCOL.md` — **no change** (output contract unchanged); state this explicitly in the PR.\n\n## Risks & considerations\n\n- **Floor is an intentional behavior change (not behavior-preserving).** Unlike revision 0's\n  pure-relocation framing, swapping the strict watermark for the floor changes output: a distinct\n  same-`source_ts` quote is now **kept** where it was dropped. This is the *point* of the operator's\n  steer; it is covered by a new explicit unit test and the migrated `tests/dedup.rs` assertions, and\n  it does not affect the PROTOCOL.md surface (still full-state, self-healing).\n- **Content-identity match across transports.** Dedup of equal-`source_ts` mirror copies only works if\n  the public px/sz rescale produces the *same* normalized tuple as the edge codec. A rescale mismatch\n  would let a duplicate through. Mitigation: unit-test the rescale against known edge-decoded values\n  for the carried coins; the E2E `no_business_duplicates` oracle catches any residual drift.\n- **Shared mutable state across tasks.** The arbiter is on the emit path of every receiver and the\n  feeder; multiple tasks now contend on one `Mutex` instead of each owning private state. Keep the\n  critical section tiny (the floor/dedup decision only) and `emit` panic-free (no `unwrap` on user\n  data) so a panic can't poison the lock. Existing single-feed throughput is unaffected (lock is\n  uncontended in the common single-receiver path).\n- **Public-feed failure isolation.** Reconnect storms / decode errors must never block multicast. The\n  feeder is a separate task; failures back off and retry, never propagate.\n- **Unbounded public lag.** A long public reconnect can deliver very stale `source_ts`, which the\n  floor rejects (`< floor`) — correct for steady state, but a public copy that is *both* stale and\n  arrives during an edge gap could still be dropped. This is the window/lag failure mode the issue\n  explicitly defers to **#30** (window sizing); call it out, do not solve it here.\n- **Instrument definition availability.** A public quote needs its `(venue, symbol)` instrument already\n  in the snapshot to satisfy `instrument_before_price`. We rely on the edge feed's refdata being\n  healthy while its mktdata stalls (the realistic backstop scenario); document the assumption and the\n  standalone-public limitation.\n- **TLS dependency surface.** Pick the `rustls`-based feature (no system OpenSSL) for portable\n  container builds.\n- **HL subscription/connection limits.** Verify the documented per-connection subscription cap and\n  fan-out within one connection; log if the configured coin set would exceed it.\n\n## Testing strategy\n\n- `cargo test` — existing codec round-trips, refdata state machine, and the multi-publisher dedup\n  tests (`tests/dedup.rs`) stay green after migration to the floor + arbiter.\n- New arbiter/floor unit tests: stale-reject (`< floor`), advance (`> floor`), **distinct\n  same-`source_ts` admitted**, **identical same-`source_ts` dropped** (cross-source collapse),\n  per-`(venue, symbol)` independence; trade `trade_id` dedup unchanged.\n- New E2E (`tests/ws_input_arbitrage.rs`): drive the release binary with both the multicast replayer\n  and the mock WS input driver; assert `no_business_duplicates` + the two backstop cases.\n- `cargo clippy --all-targets` and `cargo fmt` clean.\n\n## Estimated scope (single PR)\n\n| Stage | Area | Est. lines added (code, non-test/doc) |\n|------|------|------------------------|\n| A | shared arbiter + floor refactor | ~120–160 |\n| B | WS feeder + px/sz rescale + TLS + wiring | ~230–260 |\n| C | harness + E2E | ~0–20 code (mostly tests) |\n| **Total** | | **~350–440** |\n\nComfortably under the 500-line threshold, so per work-fast mode it ships as **one PR** with three\ninternal commits (A → B → C) for review legibility. The deferred FNV/`StableBBOHash` bit-compat path\n(~80–100 lines + an oracle change) is **out of scope** for this PR.\n\n## Open questions (defaults assumed; operator can override at re-review)\n\n1. **Floor semantics** — assumed **staleness floor + bridge-local content identity** as specified in\n   \"Design: the floor\" (reject `< floor`; collapse identical at-`floor` copies; keep distinct\n   at-`floor` updates). I found **no existing `floor` in the tree** — HEAD still ships the strict-`>`\n   `Watermark` — so this PR *implements* the floor and removes the watermark. If a floor primitive\n   already exists elsewhere, the plan reuses it unchanged. **Confirm this matches the intended floor.**\n2. **Content identity = bit-compatible with the offline board?** Assumed **no** (lean, bridge-local\n   stable hash; FNV/`StableBBOHash` bit-compat deferred to a follow-up). Override if live-bridge ↔\n   offline-analytics bit-identical dedup is required now (+~80–100 lines, deliberate oracle change).\n3. **One PR vs. stacked** — assumed **one PR** (under 500, work-fast mode) with A → B → C as internal\n   commits; #8 closes with it.\n","userModified":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Q3i6cDpz7ZNe7mKn6DHXLj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"STATUS: COMPLETE\n\nThe revised plan is written to `docs/work-plan-8.md`. Here is the full revised plan:\n\n---\n\n# Work Plan — Issue #8: Phase 3 WebSocket input feeder for public-API arbitrage\n\n> Roadbike planning artifact. Not committed (git-excluded via `.git/info/exclude`).\n> **Revision 2** — rewritten against the **updated base PR #29** (head `de61ad5`), which replaced the strict watermark with a **latch-to-leader floor** (`StalenessFloor<K, V, P>`) keyed on a publisher `P`. Operator steer: the public HL feed becomes **just another publisher racing for each slot** in that existing floor — no new dedup primitive, and the content-identity question is now moot.\n\n## Summary\n\nAdd the Hyperliquid **public** BBO/trades feed (`wss://api.hyperliquid.xyz/ws`) as a second ingest source emitting the same `FeedMessage`s into the same broadcast channel. PR #29 already turned the quote path into a **per-`(venue, symbol)` latch-to-leader floor**: within one `source_ts` tick, only the *leader* publisher (first to open that tick) is emitted; every other publisher's sample at that tick is dropped; the leader is re-selected each new tick. Edge multicast publishers already race through it by source IP.\n\nThe whole issue is therefore: **make the public WS feed one more publisher in that same floor.** Edge publishers deliver each tick sub-millisecond; the public feed arrives tens of ms later, so an edge publisher essentially always leads each tick and the public copy is dropped as a non-leader. When the edge gaps, no edge publisher opens the next tick, so the public sample is first to cross the floor (`source_ts > high_water`) — it leads and fills in. The backstop falls out of the existing floor with **no health check and no content matching**. PROTOCOL.md is unchanged.\n\nOne structural change: PR #29's floor lives **inside `TobProcessor`** (one per feed). For the public feed to race in the *same* floor as the edge HL feed, the floor and trade `WindowedDedup` must be **lifted into a process-wide shared arbiter** both transports funnel through. That's Stage A.\n\n## Base-PR status / rebase note\n\nMy branch is tipped at the **old** watermark design (`6fc5463`). PR #29 was force-updated to the **latch-to-leader** design (`de61ad5`). **This work rebases onto the new PR #29 head** — the strict `Watermark` no longer exists, so there's nothing to remove; the floor already ships. Stage A only promotes the existing `StalenessFloor`/`WindowedDedup` primitives to a shared emit stage.\n\n## The content-identity question, resolved\n\nThe operator asked for a clearer explanation or a good default. Tracing `StalenessFloor::admit(...)` for an already-open tick (`source_ts == high_water`):\n\n- `publisher != leader` → **dropped immediately; `content` is never looked at.**\n- `publisher == leader` → admit iff `content` is new **in the leader's own set** (drops that publisher's exact repeats).\n\nSo `content` is only ever compared **within a single publisher's own stream**. Two publishers' contents are never compared — the non-leader loses on identity before content is consulted. The public feed's content therefore does **not** need to equal the edge feed's content; there is nothing to make bit-compatible.\n\n**Choice (default):** drop the cross-source content-matching requirement and the canonical-exponent rescale entirely. The feeder computes content the uniform way (over normalized BBO `f64`s) only so the floor drops the public feed's *own* repeats when it leads during a gap. px/sz parse to real-unit `f64`s directly. Bit-identical dedup with the offline `hl-bbo-feed-race` board is a separate follow-up if ever needed.\n\n## Approach (single PR, three internal commits A → B → C)\n\n**A. Lift the floor + trade dedup into a shared pre-broadcast arbiter.** An `Arbiter` owns the `broadcast::Sender` plus the existing `StalenessFloor` (quotes, `P = Publisher`) and `WindowedDedup` (trades), exposing `emit(msg, publisher)`. Wrapped `Arc<Mutex<Arbiter>>` so every receiver task and the feeder converge on one floor per `(venue, symbol)`. Add `enum Publisher { Edge(IpAddr), PublicWs }`. `TobProcessor` drops its dedup state and calls `ctx.emit(...)`. **Behavior-preserving for the edge path** — a pure relocation.\n\n**B. WS-client feeder task.** New `src/ingest/ws_feeder.rs` connects over TLS, subscribes `bbo`/`trades` per coin on one connection, decodes to `FeedMessage` (`time` ms → `source_ts_ns`, so both copies land in the same floor tick), parses px/sz to real-unit `f64`s, gates on the `(venue, symbol)` instrument in the shared `InstrumentSnapshot`, and emits as `Publisher::PublicWs`. Reconnect/backoff, errors isolated, off by default.\n\n**C. Mock-WS harness + backstop E2E.** Scripted HL WS driver + two cases: edge-leads-in-steady-state (public dropped, `no_business_duplicates` green) and edge-gap → public-leads.\n\n## Estimated scope\n\n| Stage | Area | Est. lines (code) |\n|---|---|---|\n| A | shared arbiter + `Publisher` enum | ~120–150 |\n| B | WS feeder (parse-to-`f64`, no rescale) + TLS + wiring | ~180–210 |\n| C | harness + E2E | ~0–20 (mostly tests) |\n| **Total** | | **~300–380** |\n\nUnder 500 lines — one PR, three internal commits (A → B → C). Lower than rev. 1 because the floor already exists and the canonical-exponent rescale is gone.\n\n## Open questions (defaults assumed)\n\n1. **Content identity** — resolved: no bit-compatible content, no rescale; publisher-leadership decides every cross-source race.\n2. **Publisher identity type** — assumed `enum Publisher { Edge(IpAddr), PublicWs }`; alternative is a sentinel `IpAddr`.\n3. **Shared arbiter vs. share-only-the-floor** — assumed the clean shared `Arbiter` emit stage.\n\n---\n\nThe three risk/behavior notes worth flagging for re-review: the refactor is behavior-preserving for the edge path (guardrail = `tests/dedup.rs` stays green), the public feed leads only on a genuine gap, and gap-recovery correctly drops stale edge frames until edge catches past the public high-water mark. I did **not** proceed to implementation."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8585,"cache_read_input_tokens":69397,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":8585},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"global"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0e0cfeb0-baf3-4b7d-9735-46f33d7f33c8","uuid":"9b6b2e3e-e98a-45c8-be90-9d5697f4bad2","request_id":"req_011Cc9ziNiEWDEQCoh9NcERF"}
